.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:7434:Description: Phase 003 positions `board.json` as the canonical execution ledger with status transitions, but the implementation only initializes `status` once and later renders it verbatim. `updateBoard()` merges segments and findings, yet never advances board-level status from `initialized` to `planning`/`executing`/`merging`/`completed`. That leaves the “canonical” ledger stale and forces lifecycle truth to live elsewhere.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:7436:Recommendation: Add one authoritative board transition API, or have lifecycle helpers write board status on every phase change. Then add tests that assert real status progression through planning, execution, merge, completion, and failure.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:7495:Description: Phase 003 positions `board.json` as the canonical execution ledger with status transitions, but the implementation only initializes `status` once and later renders it verbatim. `updateBoard()` merges segments and findings, yet never advances board-level status from `initialized` to `planning`/`executing`/`merging`/`completed`. That leaves the “canonical” ledger stale and forces lifecycle truth to live elsewhere.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:7497:Recommendation: Add one authoritative board transition API, or have lifecycle helpers write board status on every phase change. Then add tests that assert real status progression through planning, execution, merge, completion, and failure.
