e shared SQLite store?\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:93:- D5: Does any loop phase (init / iteration / convergence / synthesis) actively READ from the coverage graph (`coverage-graph-query.ts`, `coverage-graph-convergence.cjs`) to inform decisions, or only WRITE to it?\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:96:- D5: Does the coverage graph's contribution to the 3-signal convergence math exceed its weight, or is it merely nominal?\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:321:### A command-doc requirement to invoke structural graph tools before or during iterations; the inspected command surfaces only bootstrap CocoIndex. -- BLOCKED (iteration 15, 1 attempts)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:322:- What was tried: A command-doc requirement to invoke structural graph tools before or during iterations; the inspected command surfaces only bootstrap CocoIndex.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:324:- Do NOT retry: A command-doc requirement to invoke structural graph tools before or during iterations; the inspected command surfaces only bootstrap CocoIndex.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:366:### I did not find a shipped orchestrator implementation file that performs the promised “replay journal + coverage graph + registry before dispatch,” so this pass had to prove absence via reducer inputs and helper interfaces rather than a single end-to-end resume driver. -- BLOCKED (iteration 12, 1 attempts)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:367:- What was tried: I did not find a shipped orchestrator implementation file that performs the promised “replay journal + coverage graph + registry before dispatch,” so this pass had to prove absence via reducer inputs and helper interfaces rather than a single end-to-end resume driver.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:369:- Do NOT retry: I did not find a shipped orchestrator implementation file that performs the promised “replay journal + coverage graph + registry before dispatch,” so this pass had to prove absence via reducer inputs and helper interfaces rather than a single end-to-end resume driver.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:608:- I did not find a shipped orchestrator implementation file that performs the promised “replay journal + coverage graph + registry before dispatch,” so this pass had to prove absence via reducer inputs and helper interfaces rather than a single end-to-end resume driver. (iteration 12)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:617:- A command-doc requirement to invoke structural graph tools before or during iterations; the inspected command surfaces only bootstrap CocoIndex. (iteration 15)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:677:- Mutation coverage graph uses `loop_type: \\\"improvement\\\"` namespace (shared SQLite store)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md:6:  - \\\"semantic coverage graph\\\"\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md:22:Phase 002 turns semantic convergence from an abstract idea into a concrete implementation plan. The coverage graph is the fourth graph system in the existing Spec Kit Memory stack, following the causal graph, the code structural graph, and the graph-signal layer already present under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md:78:Define an implementation-ready semantic coverage graph that reuses existing graph infrastructure, persists loop-scoped graph state in `deep-loop-graph.sqlite`, and feeds graph-backed convergence into the existing Phase 001 stop-decision logic without replacing `newInfoRatio` or other established runtime-truth signals.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md:120:| `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts` | Create | SQLite bootstrap, schema versioning, migrations, idempotent upsert support, and snapshot persistence for `deep-loop-graph.sqlite`. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md:148:| `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/coverage-graph-db.vitest.ts` | Create | Verify schema creation, namespace isolation, idempotent upsert behavior, and snapshot persistence. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md:341:| REQ-003 | Research coverage graphs MUST use the defined node kinds, relation types, initial weight estimates, and metadata contract. | `QUESTION`, `FINDING`, `CLAIM`, and `SOURCE` are canonical; all listed research relations appear unchanged; initial weight estimates are documented as inherited starting points and a calibration task is carried through plan/tasks; research metrics use the defined formulas. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md:342:| REQ-004 | Review coverage graphs MUST use the defined node kinds, relation types, initial weight estimates, and metadata contract. | `DIMENSION`, `FILE`, `FINDING`, `EVIDENCE`, and `REMEDIATION` are canonical; all listed review relations appear unchanged; initial weight estimates are documented as inherited starting points and a calibration task is carried through plan/tasks; review metrics use the defined formulas. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md:353:| REQ-010 | Human-readable graph status summaries MUST be part of the contract, not a debugging afterthought. | `deep_loop_graph_status` returns documented counts and signal summaries suitable for dashboards and synthesis surfaces; standalone visualization is deferred to a later phase. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md:361:- **SC-001**: The phase documents the coverage graph as the fourth graph system in the Spec Kit Memory stack and clearly reuses existing graph patterns.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md:455:- As a maintainer of deep review, I want coverage graph queries that show which files, dimensions, and findings still need evidence so reducer decisions stay explainable.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:4:sessionId: rvw-2026-04-12T11-30-00Z\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:32:This bundle delivered runtime truth, semantic coverage graph, wave execution, and offline optimization across ~200 files and +19K lines for sk-deep-research, sk-deep-review, and sk-improve-agent.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:59:Prior session context: A previous 10-iteration review (rvw-2026-04-11T13-50-06Z) found 16 findings (0 P0 / 10 P1 / 6 P2) with CONDITIONAL verdict. That review led to a 5-lane remediation (REQ-026 through REQ-034). This session validates the remediation AND examines areas not previously covered.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:642:    16\\t * Check whether a value looks like an in-memory coverage graph.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:777:   151\\t * @param {{ nodes: Map, edges: Map }} graph - In-memory coverage graph\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:826:   200\\t * @param {{ nodes: Map, edges: Map }} graph - In-memory coverage graph\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:860:   234\\t * @param {{ nodes: Map, edges: Map }} graph - In-memory coverage graph\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:895:     7\\t// Provides edge management primitives for in-memory coverage graphs\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:944:    56\\t * Check whether a value looks like an in-memory coverage graph.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:967:    79\\t * Create a fresh, empty coverage graph.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:979:    91\\t  if (typeof node.s