    17	<!-- Keywords: deep-improvement, deep-improvement, agent-improvement, benchmark-harness, score-candidate, promote-candidate, rollback-candidate -->
    18	
    19	# Recursive Agent: Evaluator-First Improvement Orchestrator
    20	
    21	Evaluator-first workflow for testing whether a bounded agent surface can be improved without immediately mutating the source of truth. It combines packet-local candidates, deterministic scoring, repeatable benchmarks, and explicit promotion or rollback gates.
    22	
    23	---
    24	
    25	## 1. WHEN TO USE
    26	
    27	### Three Co-Equal Lanes
    28	
    29	This skill supports three co-equal use-case lanes that share the same candidate, dispatcher, and scorer seams:
    30	
    31	| Lane | Pick when | Command |
    32	| --- | --- | --- |
    33	| **Lane A: Agent-Improvement** | You want to improve a bounded agent `.md` file | `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` |
    34	| **Lane B: Model-Benchmark** | You want to benchmark a model or prompt framework | `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` |
    35	| **Lane C: Skill-Benchmark** | You want to diagnose a skill's real-world routing, discovery, efficiency, and usefulness | `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop` |
    36	
    37	Lane A is detailed in §3 (Runtime Initialization, Proposal and Evaluation, Promotion and Recovery). Lane B is detailed in §4. Lane C (skill-benchmark) is documented in `references/skill-benchmark/` (operator guide, scoring contract, scenario authoring) and run via `loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark`. All three lanes run the same loop shape and keep the agent-improvement path byte-identical when no mode flag is set.
    38	
    39	### Activation Triggers
    40	
    41	Use this skill when:
    42	- You want to test whether an agent prompt or instruction surface can be improved (Lane A)
    43	- You want to benchmark a model or prompt framework against repeatable fixtures (Lane B)
    44	- You want to diagnose whether a skill is well-routed, discoverable, efficient, and useful in practice (Lane C)
    45	- The mutation boundary is explicit and narrow
    46	- You need packet-local evidence instead of ad hoc prompt tweaking
    47	- You need target-specific benchmark or scoring rules before any canonical mutation
    48	- Promotion must stay gated behind independent evidence plus operator approval
    49	
    50	### Primary Use Cases
    51	
    52	#### Bounded Agent Improvement
    53	
    54	Use this skill to set up a proposal-first loop for any bounded agent file, write packet-local candidates, and record append-only evidence.
    55	
    56	#### Benchmark-Backed Evaluation
    57	
    58	Use this skill when candidate quality must be judged by produced artifacts and repeatability reports, not just by how a prompt file reads in isolation.
    59	
    60	#### Promotion and Rollback Verification
    61	
    62	Use this skill when you need to prove that guarded promotion, validation, rollback, and post-rollback comparison all work end to end without leaving hidden drift behind.
    63	
    64	#### Model and Prompt Benchmarking
    65	
    66	Use Lane B (model-benchmark) when the thing under test is a model or prompt framework rather than an agent definition. It runs the same loop shape against a benchmark profile and scores produced outputs, sharing the candidate, dispatcher, and scorer seams with the agent-improvement path. See §4 below.
    67	
    68	#### Skill Benchmarking
    69	
    70	Use Lane C (skill-benchmark) when the thing under test is a *skill* — to measure whether AIs actually get routed to it, discover its references/assets unprompted, use it efficiently, and benefit from it. It emits a ranked, remediable Skill Benchmark Report and is diagnostic by default (it does not mutate the target skill). See `references/skill-benchmark/operator_guide.md`.
    71	
    72	### When NOT to Use
    73	
    74	Do not use this skill for:
    75	- Open-ended prompt rewrites across multiple agent families at once
    76	- Direct canonical edits without a packet-local candidate and evaluator evidence
    77	- Broad runtime-mirror synchronization work presented as benchmark truth
    78	- General packet planning that belongs in `/speckit:plan` or implementation that does not need an improvement loop
    79	
    80	---
    81	
    82	## 2. SMART ROUTING
    83	
    84	
    85	### Resource Domains
    86	
    87	The router discovers markdown resources recursively from `references/` and `assets/`, then applies intent scoring so only the guidance that matches the current task is loaded.
    88	
    89	- `references/` for operator workflows, evaluator policy, promotion or rollback rules, target onboarding, and quick-reference guidance
    90	- `assets/` for reusable runtime templates such as the charter and strategy markdown files
    91	- `scripts/` for deterministic benchmark, scoring, reduction, promotion, rollback, and drift-check helpers
    92	
    93	**Lane awareness**: resources are organized by lane. `references/agent-improvement/` + `assets/agent-improvement/` carry Lane A guidance, `references/model-benchmark/` + `assets/model-benchmark/` carry Lane B guidance, and `references/skill-benchmark/` + `assets/skill-benchmark/` carry Lane C guidance. `RESOURCE_MAP` routes the `MODEL_BENCHMARK` and `SKILL_BENCHMARK` intents to their lane references, and `RUNTIME_ASSETS` loads each lane's profile only when its intent is selected. The `ALWAYS` and shared `references/shared/` resources apply to all three lanes.
    94	
    95	### Resource Loading Levels
    96	
    97	| Level | When to Load | Resources |
    98	| --- | --- | --- |
    99	| ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | `references/shared/quick_reference.md` |
   100	| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Workflow, policy, or onboarding references |
   101	| ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request or full setup | Markdown runtime templates in `assets/` |
   102	
   103	### Smart Router Pseudocode
   104	
   105	The authoritative routing logic for scoped markdown loading and explicit runtime-asset loading.
   106	
   107	- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively scans `references/` and `assets/`.
   108	- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` uses `_guard_in_skill()`, `inventory`, and `seen`.
   109	- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - quick-reference, loop, evaluation, promotion, target onboarding, integration, and setup intents route resources.
   110	- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST` asks for target/action/gate disambiguation and missing intent routes return a "no knowledge base" notice.
   111	
   112	```python
   113	from pathlib import Path
   114	
   115	SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent
   116	RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / "references", SKILL_ROOT / "assets")
   117	DEFAULT_RESOURCE = "references/shared/quick_reference.md"
   118	
   119	INTENT_SIGNALS = {
   120	    "QUICK_REFERENCE": {"weight": 3, "keywords": ["quick reference", "short reminder", "command example"]},
   121	    "LOOP_EXECUTION": {"weight": 4, "keywords": ["run loop", "proposal", "candidate", "score candidate", "benchmark"]},
   122	    "EVALUATION_POLICY": {"weight": 4, "keywords": ["evaluator", "rubric", "contract", "repeatability", "no-go"]},
   123	    "PROMOTION_OPERATIONS": {"weight": 4, "keywords": ["promote", "rollback", "mirror drift", "approval gate"]},
   124	    "TARGET_ONBOARDING": {"weight": 4, "keywords": ["new target", "target profile", "onboarding", "second target"]},
   125	    "INTEGRATION_SCAN": {"weight": 4, "keywords": ["integration", "scan surfaces", "mirror sync", "dynamic profile", "5-dimension"]},
   126	    "MODEL_BENCHMARK": {"weight": 5, "keywords": ["benchmark a model", "benchmark a prompt framework", "optimize a model", "model-benchmark", "model benchmark"]},
   127	    "SKILL_BENCHMARK": {"weight": 5, "keywords": ["benchmark a skill", "skill benchmark", "skill routing", "unprompted discovery", "routing accuracy", "skill-benchmark"]},
   128	    "FULL_SETUP": {"weight": 3, "keywords": ["full setup", "initialize runtime", "charter", "strategy"]},
   129	}
   130	
   131	RESOURCE_MAP = {
   132	    "QUICK_REFERENCE": ["references/shared/quick_reference.md"],
   133	    "LOOP_EXECUTION": ["references/shared/loop_protocol.md", "references/model-benchmark/benchmark_operator_guide.md"],
   134	    "EVALUATION_POLICY": ["references/model-benchmark/evaluator_contract.md", "references/shared/promotion_rules.md"],
   135	    "PROMOTION_OPERATIONS": ["references/shared/rollback_runbook.md", "references/agent-improvement/mirror_drift_policy.md", "references/shared/promotion_rules.md"],
   136	    "TARGET_ONBOARDING": ["references/agent-improvement/target_onboarding.md"],
   137	    "INTEGRATION_SCAN": ["references/agent-improvement/integration_scanning.md", "references/model-benchmark/evaluator_contract.md"],
   138	    "MODEL_BENCHMARK": ["references/model-benchmark/benchmark_operator_guide.md", "references/model-benchmark/evaluator_contract.md"],
   139	    "SKILL_BENCHMARK": ["references/skill-benchmark/operator_guide.md", "references/skill-benchmark/scoring_contract.md", "references/skill-benchmark/scenario_authoring.md"],
   140	    "FULL_SETUP": ["assets/agent-improvement/improvement_charter.md", "assets/agent-improvement/improvement_strategy.md"],
   141	}
   142	
   143	RUNTIME_ASSETS = {
   144	    "ALWAYS": ["assets/agent-improvement/improvement_config.json", "assets/agent-improvement/target_manifest.jsonc"],
   145	    "MODEL_BENCHMARK": ["assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json"],
   146	    "SKILL_BENCHMARK": ["assets/skill-benchmark/default_profile.json"],
   147	}
   148	
   149	ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS = ["target profile", "score candidate", "proposal loop", "benchmark", "promotion gate", "mirror drift"]
   150	
   151	def _task_text(task) -> str:
   152	    return " ".join([
   153	        str(getattr(task, "text", "")),
   154	        str(getattr(task, "query", "")),
   155	        " ".join(getattr(task, "keywords", []) or []),
   156	    ]).lower()
   157	
   158	UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = ["Confirm target path", "Confirm proposal vs scoring vs promotion", "Confirm packet-local evidence path"]
   159	
   160	def _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:
   161	    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()
   162	    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)
   163	    if resolved.suffix.lower() != ".md":
   164	        raise ValueError(f"Only markdown resources are routed here: {relative_path}")
   165	    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()
   166	
   167	def discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:
   168	    docs = []
   169	    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:
   170	        if base.exists():
   171	            docs.extend(p for p in base.rglob("*.md") if p.is_file())
   172	    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}
   173	
   174	def score_intents(task) -> dict[str, float]:
   175	    text = _task_text(task)
   176	    scores = {intent: 0.0 for intent in INTENT_SIGNALS}
   177	    for intent, cfg in INTENT_SIGNALS.items():
   178	        for keyword in cfg["keywords"]:
   179	            if keyword in text:
   180	                scores[intent] += cfg["weight"]

