.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/implementation-summary.md:60:Lane C should measure whether a skill is **discovered, routed to, and used effectively by an AI in situ** — distinct from `sk-doc` (doc shape) and `system-skill-advisor` (which skill to pick). Recommended five scoring dimensions with weights: Routing/Activation Accuracy (0.25), Unprompted Reference/Asset Discovery (0.25), Efficiency/Bottlenecks (0.20), Usefulness-via-Ablation (0.20), Structural Connectivity (0.10); captured via a hint-free dispatch harness; reusing the existing candidate/dispatcher/scorer seams under `loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark`.
