.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:2180:.opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/04--cross-cli-dispatch/003-multi-step-dispatch.md:20:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:2188:.opencode/skills/sk-doc/README.md:89:The Flowchart mode provides seven ASCII patterns for documenting processes visually inside markdown. Each pattern has a dedicated reference file with worked examples. The patterns cover the most common documentation needs: linear step sequences, binary and multi-way decision branches, concurrent task execution, nested sub-workflows, approval and revision cycles, repeat-until loops, and multi-stage pipelines with gates. The validator (`validate_flowchart.sh`) checks alignment, consistent box styles, labeled decision branches, and complete entry/exit paths.
