.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:2251:.opencode/skills/sk-doc/manual_testing_playbook/02--resource-loading/001-references-global-only.md:15:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:2293:.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:25:The dedicated documentation executor agent renames from `@create` to `@markdown` across all four runtime mirrors: `.opencode/agents/markdown.md`, `.claude/agents/markdown.md`, `.gemini/agents/markdown.md`, and `.codex/agents/markdown.toml`. The Codex registry block updates from `[agents.create]` to `[agents.markdown]` with `config_file = "agents/markdown.toml"`. Orchestrator and code-agent references route documentation and component authoring through `@markdown`. The `/create:*` command family (`/create:agent`, `/create:sk-skill`, `/create:feature-catalog`, `/create:testing-playbook`, `/create:folder_readme`, `/create:changelog`) keeps every invocation unchanged because this is an agent identity rename, not a command-family rename.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:2300:.opencode/skills/sk-doc/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:19:The trio of benchmark format docs collapsed into one canonical reference following the sk-doc *_creation.md pattern. The references/benchmarks/FORMAT.md file at 384 LOC, the references/benchmarks_format.md file at 205 LOC, and the assets template merged into references/benchmark_creation.md at 414 LOC with 10 numbered sections from OVERVIEW through RELATED RESOURCES. The consolidated doc generalizes the Section 5 example and Q7 to remove stack-specific references like Ollama, cat-24/409 and sentence-transformers so the guidance is portable across MCP skills. The mid-flight redesign was an operator decision after the first author pass.
