.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:3786:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/scratch/agent-output-iter-004-codex-A3.md:474:      "text": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/system-spec-kit/shared/parsing/README.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\ntitle: \\\"Quality Extractors\\\"\\ndescription: \\\"Shared parsing functions for extracting quality metadata from YAML frontmatter in memory files.\\\"\\ntrigger_phrases:\\n  - \\\"quality extractors\\\"\\n  - \\\"quality score parsing\\\"\\n  - \\\"frontmatter quality flags\\\"\\n---\\n\\n# Quality Extractors\\n\\n> Shared parsing functions for extracting quality metadata from YAML frontmatter in memory files.\\n\\n---\\n\\n<!-- ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\\n## TABLE OF CONTENTS\\n\\n- [1. OVERVIEW](#1-overview)\\n- [2. STRUCTURE](#2-structure)\\n- [3. RELATED DOCUMENTS](#3-related-documents)\\n\\n<!-- /ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\\n\\n---\\n\\n<!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\\n## 1. OVERVIEW\\n\\nThis module provides the canonical implementation for extracting `quality_score` and `quality_flags` from YAML frontmatter blocks. It replaces duplicate extraction logic that previously existed in `memory-indexer.ts` and `memory-parser.ts`.\\n\\n**Key behaviors:**\",\n      \"start_line\": 1,\n      \"end_line\": 32,\n      \"score\": 0.638087092785554\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/quality-loop.ts\",\n      \"language\": \"typescript\",\n      \"content\": \"/**\\n * Compute composite quality score for a memory file.\\n *\\n * Aggregates the four dimension sub-scores into a single weighted total using\\n * the weights defined in `QUALITY_WEIGHTS`:\\n *   - triggers  × 0.25\\n *   - anchors   × 0.30\\n *   - budget    × 0.20\\n *   - coherence × 0.25\",\n      \"start_line\": 361,\n      \"end_line\": 369,\n      \"score\": 0.6122033943237284\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/audits/audit-C15.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"    19\\t * Canonical shared implementation — replaces duplicates in memory-indexer.ts and memory-parser.ts.\\n    20\\t */\\n succeeded in 50ms:\\n     1\\t---\\n     2\\ttitle: \\\"Quality Extractors\\\"\\n     3\\tdescription: \\\"Shared parsing functions for extracting quality metadata from YAML frontmatter in memory files.\\\"\\n     4\\ttrigger_phrases:\\n     5\\t  - \\\"quality extractors\\\"\\n     6\\t  - \\\"quality score parsing\\\"\\n     7\\t  - \\\"frontmatter quality flags\\\"\\n     8\\t---\\n     9\\t\\n    10\\t# Quality Extractors\\n    11\\t\\n    12\\t> Shared parsing functions for extracting quality metadata from YAML frontmatter in memory files.\",\n      \"start_line\": 348,\n      \"end_line\": 362,\n      \"score\": 0.6087537195498669\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/system-spec-kit/shared/parsing/quality-extractors.ts\",\n      \"language\": \"typescript\",\n      \"content\": \"export function extractQualityScore(content: string): number {\\n  const fm = extractFrontmatter(content);\\n  const match = fm.match(/quality_score:\\\\s*([0-9.]+)/i);\\n  if (!match) return 0;\\n  const parsed = Number.parseFloat(match[1]);\\n  if (!Number.isFinite(parsed)) return 0;\\n  return Math.max(0, Math.min(1, parsed));\\n}\\n\\n/**\\n * Extract quality flags from frontmatter content.\\n * Canonical shared implementation — replaces duplicates in memory-indexer.ts and memory-parser.ts.\\n */\\nexport function extractQualityFlags(content: string): string[] {\\n  const fm = extractFrontmatter(content);\\n  const blockMatch = fm.match(/quality_flags:\\\\s*\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)(?:\\\\n\\\\S|$)/i);\\n  if (!blockMatch) return [];\\n  const lines = blockMatch[1].split('\\\\n');\\n  const flags: string[] = [];\\n  for (const line of lines) {\\n    const flagMatch = line.match(/^\\\\s*-\\\\s*['\\\"]?([^'\\\"]+)['\\\"]?\\\\s*$/);\\n    if (flagMatch) flags.push(flagMatch[1].trim());\\n  }\\n  return flags;\\n}\",\n      \"start_line\": 21,\n      \"end_line\": 45,\n      \"score\": 0.6063045454032174\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/eval-ceiling.ts\",\n      \"language\": \"typescript\",\n      \"content\": \"  if (!highCeiling && !highBaseline) {\\n    return {\\n      quadrant: 'low-ceiling-low-baseline',\\n      interpretation: 'Data quality issue — improve memory content before algorithm changes',\\n      recommendation:\\n        'The theoretical ceiling is low, meaning even a perfect ranker cannot achieve good MRR. Prioritise improving memory titles, summaries, and ground truth coverage before tuning the retrieval algorithm.',\\n    };\\n  }\\n\\n  // !highCeiling && highBaseline\\n  return {\\n    quadrant: 'low-ceiling-high-baseline',\\n    interpretation: 'Near optimal — system is close to data quality ceiling',\\n    recommendation:\\n      'The system is performing near the theoretical maximum given current memory quality. To improve further, enrich memory content (titles, summaries) and expand ground truth annotations.',\\n  };\\n}\",\n      \"start_line\": 366,\n      \"end_line\": 382,\n      \"score\": 0.5782268261983301\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/analysis/analysis-X02.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"     2\\t// MODULE: Quality Extractors\\n     3\\t// ---------------------------------------------------------------\\n     4\\t\\n     5\\tconst FRONTMATTER_RE = /^---\\\\r?\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)\\\\r?\\\\n---(?:\\\\r?\\\\n|$)/;\\n     6\\t\\n     7\\t/**\\n     8\\t * Extract the YAML frontmatter block (between --- delimiters).\\n     9\\t * Returns empty string when no frontmatter is found — body text must never\\n    10\\t * be parsed as metadata (T040 acceptance criteria).\\n    11\\t */\\n    12\\tfunction extractFrontmatter(content: string): string {\\n    13\\t  const match = content.match(FRONTMATTER_RE);\\n    14\\t  return match ? match[1] : '';\\n    15\\t}\\n    16\\t\\n    17\\t/**\\n    18\\t * Extract quality score from frontmatter content.\\n    19\\t * Canonical shared implementation — replaces duplicates in memory-indexer.ts and memory-parser.ts.\\n    20\\t */\\nexec\",\n      \"start_line\": 840,\n      \"end_line\": 859,\n      \"score\": 0.5756131547805818\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/audits/audit-C08.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"     2\\t// MODULE: Quality Extractors\\n     3\\t// ---------------------------------------------------------------\\n     4\\t\\n     5\\tconst FRONTMATTER_RE = /^---\\\\r?\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)\\\\r?\\\\n---(?:\\\\r?\\\\n|$)/;\\n     6\\t\\n     7\\t/**\\n     8\\t * Extract the YAML frontmatter block (between --- delimiters).\\n     9\\t * Returns empty string when no frontmatter is found — body text must never\\n    10\\t * be parsed as metadata (T040 acceptance criteria).\\n    11\\t */\\n    12\\tfunction extractFrontmatter(content: string): string {\\n    13\\t  const match = content.match(FRONTMATTER_RE);\\n    14\\t  return match ? match[1] : '';\\n    15\\t}\\n    16\\t\\n    17\\t/**\\n    18\\t * Extract quality score from frontmatter content.\\n    19\\t * Canonical shared implementation — replaces duplicates in memory-indexer.ts and memory-parser.ts.\\n    20\\t */\\n succeeded in 51ms:\",\n      \"start_line\": 296,\n      \"end_line\": 315,\n      \"score\": 0.5756131547805818\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/audits/audit-C14.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"     2\\t// MODULE: Quality Extractors\\n     3\\t// ---------------------------------------------------------------\\n     4\\t\\n     5\\tconst FRONTMATTER_RE = /^---\\\\r?\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)\\\\r?\\\\n---(?:\\\\r?\\\\n|$)/;\\n     6\\t\\n     7\\t/**\\n     8\\t * Extract the YAML frontmatter block (between --- delimiters).\\n     9\\t * Returns empty string when no frontmatter is found — body text must never\\n    10\\t * be parsed as metadata (T040 acceptance criteria).\\n    11\\t */\\n    12\\tfunction extractFrontmatter(content: string): string {\\n    13\\t  const match = content.match(FRONTMATTER_RE);\\n    14\\t  return match ? match[1] : '';\\n    15\\t}\\n    16\\t\\n    17\\t/**\\n    18\\t * Extract quality score from frontmatter content.\\n    19\\t * Canonical shared implementation — replaces duplicates in memory-indexer.ts and memory-parser.ts.\\n    20\\t */\\nexec\",\n      \"start_line\": 226,\n      \"end_line\": 245,\n      \"score\": 0.5756131547805818\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total_returned\": 8,\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"message\": null\n}"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:3788:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/scratch/agent-output-iter-004-codex-A3.md:496:      "text": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/analysis/analysis-X02.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"- **Severity:** CRITICAL\\n- **Category:** BUG\\n- **Current Behavior:** Workflow injects `quality_score` and `quality_flags` into the machine-readable fenced YAML block, but the shared parser used by indexing reads only top frontmatter, so the indexed quality metadata resolves to `0` / `[]`. The workflow also returns the legacy `0-100` score in `stats.qualityScore`, so the two scorers can contradict on the same memory.\\n- **Expected Behavior:** One consistent quality signal should be embedded, indexed, and returned on one documented scale.\\n- **Root Cause:** Writer and reader disagree about where quality metadata lives, and workflow exposes the other scorer’s units.\\n- **Suggested Fix:** Either move injected quality metadata into frontmatter or teach the shared parser to read the machine-readable YAML block first; then return the same normalized score from workflow stats.\\n- **Effort:** MEDIUM (<2 hr)\",\n      \"start_line\": 1060,\n      \"end_line\": 1066,\n      \"score\": 0.621489633012736\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/analysis/analysis-X02.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"- **Severity:** CRITICAL\\n- **Category:** BUG\\n- **Current Behavior:** Workflow injects `quality_score` and `quality_flags` into the machine-readable fenced YAML block, but the shared parser used by indexing reads only top frontmatter, so the indexed quality metadata resolves to `0` / `[]`. The workflow also returns the legacy `0-100` score in `stats.qualityScore`, so the two scorers can contradict on the same memory.\\n- **Expected Behavior:** One consistent quality signal should be embedded, indexed, and returned on one documented scale.\\n- **Root Cause:** Writer and reader disagree about where quality metadata lives, and workflow exposes the other scorer’s units.\\n- **Suggested Fix:** Either move injected quality metadata into frontmatter or teach the shared parser to read the machine-readable YAML block first; then return the same normalized score from workflow stats.\\n- **Effort:** MEDIUM (<2 hr)\",\n      \"start_line\": 1156,\n      \"end_line\": 1162,\n      \"score\": 0.621489633012736\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/001-quality-scorer-unification/spec.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\\n\\n### Problem Statement\\n\\nThe pipeline runs three quality checks with a split contract: stored/indexed quality uses the 0.0-1.0 scale, but workflow gating uses 0-100. The `qualityAbortThreshold` config is validated as 1-100 with a default of 15. The V1 scorer covers 7 dimensions on the 0-100 scale. The V2 scorer covers 9 dimensions on 0.0-1.0. Neither scorer accounts for contamination detection results -- contamination produces a flag but no score penalty.\\n\\n### Purpose\\n\\nMake `score01` (0.0-1.0) the canonical quality scale across the entire pipeline, keep `score100` as a backward-compatible alias, migrate the abort threshold to the canonical scale, and ensure contamination detection produces a measurable score penalty rather than just a boolean flag.\\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\\n\\n---\\n\\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\",\n      \"start_line\": 49,\n      \"end_line\": 62,\n      \"score\": 0.5833183569593245\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/qa/qa-08-p1-fixes-part2.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"### FINDING-13: workflow.ts Step 8.7 Quality Abort Gate — INCORRECT\\n- **File:** `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/core/workflow.ts:881-888`\\n- **Severity:** HIGH\\n- **Category:** ALIGNMENT\\n- **Current Behavior:** The workflow aborts when `qualityResult.score < 25` (and not simulation).\\n- **Expected Behavior:** Abort only when the score is below `15`.\\n- **Root Cause:** `QUALITY_ABORT_THRESHOLD` is set to `25`, not `15`.\\n- **Suggested Fix:** Change `const QUALITY_ABORT_THRESHOLD = 25;` to `15`, and verify any tests/docs expecting the stricter threshold.\\n- **Effort:** TRIVIAL (<5 min)\",\n      \"start_line\": 178,\n      \"end_line\": 186,\n      \"score\": 0.5766473066905728\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/001-quality-scorer-unification/implementation-summary.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"<!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->\\n\\n---\\n\\n<!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\\n## 3. HOW IT WAS DELIVERED\\n\\n1. Defined the unified `QualityScoreResult` interface in `core/quality-scorer.ts` with both scales, then had `extractors/quality-scorer.ts` import and re-export the types instead of duplicating them.\\n2. Added the contamination penalty in the V2 scorer matching the spec: `qualityScore -= 0.25` and `sufficiencyCap = Math.min(sufficiencyCap ?? 1, 0.6)`.\\n3. Added `normalizeQualityAbortThreshold()` to auto-detect integer thresholds (>1) and convert by dividing by 100, with a deprecation warning.\\n4. Migrated all workflow quality comparisons from `score` (0-100) to `score01` (0.0-1.0).\\n<!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\\n\\n---\\n\\n<!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\",\n      \"start_line\": 36,\n      \"end_line\": 51,\n      \"score\": 0.5749369601430772\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/015-outsourced-agent-handback/memory/16-03-26_22-31__completed-phase-015-by-aligning-the-outsourced.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"## 4. DECISIONS\\n\\n<!-- ANCHOR:decision-document-distinction-between-qualitygateabort-82a0452a -->\\n### Decision 1: Document the distinction between QUALITY_GATE_ABORT and non\\n\\n**Context**: blocking QUALITY_GATE_FAIL for file-backed handbacks so callers understand why a write can succeed while indexing is skipped.\\n\\n**Timestamp**: 2026-03-16T22:31:51Z\\n\\n**Importance**: medium\\n\\n#### Options Considered\\n\\n1. **Chosen Approach**\\n   Document the distinction between QUALITY_GATE_ABORT and non\\n\\n#### Chosen Approach\\n\\n**Selected**: Document the distinction between QUALITY_GATE_ABORT and non\\n\\n**Rationale**: blocking QUALITY_GATE_FAIL for file-backed handbacks so callers understand why a write can succeed while indexing is skipped.\\n\\n#### Trade-offs\\n\\n**Confidence**: 50%\\n\\n<!-- /ANCHOR:decision-document-distinction-between-qualitygateabort-82a0452a -->\\n\\n---\\n\\n<!-- ANCHOR:decision-dedicated-doc-regression-test-df04a0fe -->\",\n      \"start_line\": 264,\n      \"end_line\": 294,\n      \"score\": 0.5661644076296977\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/agent-outputs/stateless-research/RCA-memory-corruption-investigation.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"### H7 — Two Quality Scores on Different Scales Write to the Same Conceptual Field (Quality-Score Conflict)\\n**Hypothesis:** `metadata.json`'s `filtering.qualityScore: 30` and the frontmatter `quality_score: 0.85` are produced by two completely different scoring systems:  \\n- **30/100** = `filterPipeline.getStats().qualityScore` (content filter pipeline, 0–100 scale) measuring message noise/deduplication quality. Stored at `workflow.ts:941` inside the `filtering` key of metadata.json.  \\n- **0.85/1.00** = `qualityV2.qualityScore` from `scoreMemoryQualityV2()` (structural validator, 0.0–1.0 scale) measuring rendered markdown structural compliance. Injected into frontmatter via `injectQualityMetadata()` at `workflow.ts:1008`.\\n\\nNeither output includes the scale or algorithm name. A third scorer (`scoreMemoryQuality()`, legacy 0–100) runs at line 1014 but is only logged, never persisted.\",\n      \"start_line\": 459,\n      \"end_line\": 464,\n      \"score\": 0.5599246058972938\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/001-quality-scorer-unification/checklist.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"- [x] CHK-018 [P1] `workflow.ts` compares `score01` against the migrated threshold (REQ-004) [Evidence: `scripts/core/workflow.ts` quality-gate comparison path uses canonical `score01` and normalized threshold.]\\n- [x] CHK-019 [P2] No `as any` or `as unknown` casts introduced during migration [Evidence: grep confirms zero `as any` or `as unknown` occurrences in core/quality-scorer.ts, extractors/quality-scorer.ts, core/workflow.ts, and core/config.ts.]\\n<!-- /ANCHOR:code-quality -->\\n\\n---\\n\\n<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\",\n      \"start_line\": 47,\n      \"end_line\": 53,\n      \"score\": 0.5579762526535887\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total_returned\": 8,\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"message\": null\n}"
