.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:3940:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/003-memory-and-causal-runtime/003-embedder-testing-and-architecture/009-memory-leak-remediation/001-research-synthesis-and-remediation-map/research/source-research/020-cli-process-memory-leak-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:39:15. The runtime agent `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md` frontmatter is `permission: { ... bash: deny, ... patch: deny, ... task: allow, ... }`. The skill `.opencode/skills/sk-ai-council/SKILL.md` frontmatter is `allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep]`. The two surfaces disagree on whether the council may shell out: the agent denies Bash; the skill description claims Bash is allowed. Operators reading SKILL.md may design Bash-using council workflows that the runtime rejects with a permission denial at execution time. [SOURCE: `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md:6-22`]; [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-ai-council/SKILL.md:4`]
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:3941:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/003-memory-and-causal-runtime/003-embedder-testing-and-architecture/009-memory-leak-remediation/001-research-synthesis-and-remediation-map/research/source-research/020-cli-process-memory-leak-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:75:- **Contradictory evidence:** `ai-council.md` line 17 declares `permission.bash: deny`; `sk-ai-council/SKILL.md` line 4 declares `allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep]`. Both are checked into the repo and both are "documentation of intent" — only the agent frontmatter governs the runtime. The SKILL.md is consumed by operators authoring scripts and by the skill-advisor; the drift is silent.
