.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:3976:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/scratch/agent-output-iter-003-codex-A1.md:206:      "text": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/agent-outputs/stateless-research/audit-QA5-O09-session-extractor.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"### P2-06: `detectContextType` and `detectProjectPhase` have overlapping logic\\n**File:line:** `session-extractor.ts:149-162` and `session-extractor.ts:175-194`\\n**Evidence:** Both functions compute `readTools`, `writeTools` ratios from `toolCounts` with similar but slightly different thresholds (0.5 vs 0.6 for read-heavy, 0.3 vs 0.4 for write-heavy). This is intentional (context type vs project phase are different concepts), but the similar-but-different thresholds could benefit from named constants.\",\n      \"start_line\": 185,\n      \"end_line\": 187,\n      \"score\": 0.580010950448667\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/agent-outputs/stateless-research/audit-QA5-O09-session-extractor.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"### P2-05: Duplicate `extractKeyTopics` across modules\\n**File:line:** `session-extractor.ts:370-422` vs `core/topic-extractor.ts:26-96`\\n**Evidence:** Two separate implementations exist. The session-extractor version uses flat word sorting by length, while the topic-extractor version uses weighted scoring and bigram analysis. The NOTE comment on line 365-369 documents the differences. However, no consumer imports `extractKeyTopics` from `session-extractor` — only from `core/topic-extractor` (via workflow.ts:23). The session-extractor version is exported (line 472) and tested (test-extractors-loaders.js:492), but appears unused in production code.\\n**Impact:** Dead code increases maintenance burden. If the session-extractor version is truly unused, it should be removed. If it serves a different purpose (e.g., lightweight extraction without bigrams), that purpose should be documented more explicitly.\",\n      \"start_line\": 180,\n      \"end_line\": 183,\n      \"score\": 0.5569773469268782\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/agent-outputs/stateless-research/audit-deep-research-scratch.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"### 4.4 `detectObservationType()` Integration Path — **Identified but Not Verified**\\n\\nR07 recommends reusing `detectObservationType()` from `file-extractor.ts:92–107` inside the input normalizer. No research verifies whether this function is already reachable from `input-normalizer.ts` (circular import risk) or whether it needs to be extracted to a shared utility. The plan.md mentions this as Phase 1 work but doesn't verify the import topology.\\n\\n### 4.5 `ensureMinTriggerPhrases()` Interaction with Enrichment — **Not Covered**\\n\\nR06 identifies `ensureMinTriggerPhrases()` at `workflow.ts:113–139` as the floor preventing trigger-phrase collapse. No research analyzes whether enriched data (spec.md frontmatter `trigger_phrases` directly available) would make this floor redundant, or whether there is a risk of double-counting when both the extractor and the floor contribute trigger phrases.\",\n      \"start_line\": 317,\n      \"end_line\": 323,\n      \"score\": 0.5385749613770638\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/005-architecture-audit/scratch/agent5-architecture-analysis.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"## Near-duplicates (same intent, different implementation)\\n\\n4. Trigger extraction layers\\n- Shared canonical NLP extractor exists: `shared/trigger-extractor.ts:527-608`.\\n- MCP parser has its own trigger extractor: `mcp_server/lib/parsing/memory-parser.ts:460-524`.\\n- MCP quality loop has another lightweight extractor: `mcp_server/handlers/quality-loop.ts:343-362`.\\n- Scripts consume shared trigger extractor via shim: `scripts/lib/trigger-extractor.ts:1-7`.\\n\\nRisk: different trigger phrase derivation logic depending on pathway (scripts workflow vs MCP parser/quality loop).\",\n      \"start_line\": 54,\n      \"end_line\": 62,\n      \"score\": 0.5300654963686053\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/system-spec-kit/scripts/utils/spec-affinity.ts\",\n      \"language\": \"typescript\",\n      \"content\": \"  const normalizedText = normalizeText(rawText);\\n  const normalizedPathText = normalizePathLike(rawText);\\n\\n  const matchedFileTargets = targets.fileTargets.filter((target) => (\\n    normalizedPathText.includes(target)\\n    || normalizedPathText.endsWith(`/${target}`)\\n  ));\\n  const matchedPhrases = targets.exactPhrases.filter((phrase) => normalizedText.includes(phrase));\\n  const matchedKeywordTokens = countKeywordMatches(normalizedText, targets.strongKeywordTokens);\\n  const discoveredIds = extractSpecIds(rawText);\\n  const matchedSpecId = Boolean(targets.specId && discoveredIds.includes(targets.specId));\\n  const foreignSpecIds = discoveredIds.filter((specId) => specId !== targets.specId);\\n\\n  return {\\n    matchedFileTargets,\\n    matchedPhrases,\\n    matchedKeywordTokens,\\n    matchedSpecId,\\n    foreignSpecIds,\\n  };\\n}\",\n      \"start_line\": 362,\n      \"end_line\": 382,\n      \"score\": 0.5123462845892259\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/008-signal-extraction/checklist.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"- [x] CHK-018 [P2] Script-side duplicate stopword/topic owners removed from migrated extractors [Evidence: topic/session/summary callers now share the unified engine instead of carrying their own stopword lists.]\\n- [x] CHK-019 [P2] Trigger weighting consistent with existing trigger-extractor logic [Evidence: the engine reuses shared trigger scoring primitives and the frozen parity suite matches shared-baseline output.]\\n<!-- /ANCHOR:code-quality -->\\n\\n---\\n\\n<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\",\n      \"start_line\": 47,\n      \"end_line\": 53,\n      \"score\": 0.5091575980771221\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/semantic-signal-golden.vitest.ts\",\n      \"language\": \"typescript\",\n      \"content\": \"import { describe, expect, it } from 'vitest';\\n\\nimport { extractTriggerPhrases as sharedExtractTriggerPhrases } from '@spec-kit/shared/trigger-extractor';\\nimport { extractKeyTopics as extractWorkflowTopics } from '../core/topic-extractor';\\nimport { extractKeyTopics as extractSessionTopics } from '../extractors/session-extractor';\\nimport { SemanticSignalExtractor } from '../lib/semantic-signal-extractor';\\nimport {\\n  extractTriggerPhrases,\\n  extractTriggerPhrasesWithStats,\\n} from '../lib/trigger-extractor';\\nimport { generateImplementationSummary } from '../lib/semantic-summarizer';\",\n      \"start_line\": 1,\n      \"end_line\": 11,\n      \"score\": 0.5046248281675787\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/agent-outputs/stateless-research/R10-integration-architecture.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"### Key improvement over current behavior\\n\\nCurrent `detectRelatedDocs()` only says a file exists and labels its role [SOURCE: `scripts/extractors/session-extractor.ts:304-355`]. The new extractor should parse **content**, not just filenames.\\n\\n## 5.3 `scripts/extractors/claude-code-capture.ts`\\n\\n### Purpose\\n\\nProvide a stateless fallback conversation source when OpenCode capture is unavailable or too thin.\",\n      \"start_line\": 173,\n      \"end_line\": 181,\n      \"score\": 0.5020592424178858\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/research/agent-outputs/stateless-research/audit-QA10-O18-opus-synthesis.md\",\n      \"language\": \"markdown\",\n      \"content\": \"| 25 | O12-P1-02 | session-extractor.ts:25-37 | ToolCounts index signature masks missing required fields | O12 |\\n| 26 | O13-F03 | workflow.ts (~L843-884) | _manualTriggerPhrases stored but never consumed | O13 |\\n| 27 | O14-F02 | session-extractor.ts:74 vs file-extractor.ts:38 | Observation vs ObservationInput incompatible facts types | O14 |\\n| 28 | O14-F03 | Multiple files | FileEntry/FileChange/FileInput represent same concept with incompatible shapes | O14 |\\n| 29 | O16-P1-01 | file-extractor.ts:238-242,262-268 | enhanceFilesWithSemanticDescriptions strips provenance markers on match | O16, O13 |\\n| 30 | O16-P1-02 | file-extractor.ts:278-318 | buildObservationsWithAnchors strips all observation provenance markers | O16, O07, O13 |\",\n      \"start_line\": 244,\n      \"end_line\": 249,\n      \"score\": 0.4976743898232314\n    },\n    {\n      \"file_path\": \"specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/parsing/memory-parser.ts\",\n      \"language\": \"typescript\",\n      \"content\": \",\\n  CONTEXT_TYPE_MAP,\\n\\n  // Backward-compatible aliases (snake_case)\\n  parse_memory_file: parseMemoryFile,\\n  parse_memory_content: parseMemoryContent,\\n  read_file_with_encoding: readFileWithEncoding,\\n  extract_spec_folder: extractSpecFolder,\\n  extract_title: extractTitle,\\n  extract_trigger_phrases: extractTriggerPhrases,\\n  extract_context_type: extractContextType,\\n  extract_importance_tier: extractImportanceTier,\\n  get_canonical_path_key: getCanonicalPathKey,\\n  compute_content_hash: computeContentHash,\\n  infer_memory_type: inferMemoryType,\\n  extract_causal_links: extractCausalLinks,\\n};\",\n      \"start_line\": 953,\n      \"end_line\": 969,\n      \"score\": 0.4969177574562309\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total_returned\": 10,\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"message\": null\n}"
