.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:4021:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/001-initial-enrichment/scratch/agent-output-iter-002-A10.md:111:[INFERENCE: based on trigger phrase flow through template renderer to YAML frontmatter to BM25 index]
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:4027:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/016-json-mode-hybrid-enrichment/001-initial-enrichment/scratch/agent-output-iter-002-A7.md:48:The quality scorer has an empty content check (lines 85-106 of quality-scorer.ts) that catches completely empty content. But there is no V-rule for "content is present but trivially short" -- a rendered memory with just `# Title\n\nOne sentence.` and valid frontmatter passes all V-rules. The `short_content` quality flag exists in the type system but no V-rule triggers it. The `P3-4: minimum_message_ratio` check in the scorer partially addresses this (flagging `insufficient_capture` when message/tool ratio < 0.05), but it is a heuristic about session shape, not content adequacy.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:4031:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/scratch/codex-root-cause-memory-quality-gates.md:15:The payload explicitly supplied both `title` and `description`. The save log shows those keys were warned as unknown and ignored before normalization completed. The same save then rendered an auto-generated heading based on the slugified `sessionSummary`, and the description generator fell back to truncating summary/title text because no explicit description survived into the workflow. (`/tmp/save-context-data.json:2-4`, `/tmp/memory-save-output2.log:5-10`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/core/workflow.ts:1204-1238`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/core/title-builder.ts:44-59`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/memory-frontmatter.ts:97-122`)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:4032:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/scratch/codex-root-cause-memory-quality-gates.md:139:V8 is extraction-first, not allowlist-first. It first finds all `SPEC_ID_REGEX` matches in body/frontmatter, then subtracts the allowlist built from the current spec folder, child phases, sibling phases, and `related_specs`. Anything not in that allowlist becomes foreign contamination. That means non-spec tokens are misclassified before the allowlist even has a chance to say "this is not a spec slug." (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/validate-memory-quality.ts:209`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/validate-memory-quality.ts:478-487`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/validate-memory-quality.ts:540-594`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/validate-memory-quality.ts:741-808`)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:4033:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/scratch/agent-15-synthesis-report.md:120:**Description**: YAML frontmatter is missing `description` and `trigger_phrases` fields in phases 001-013. Only phases 014-016 have complete frontmatter.
