.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:4286:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/scratch/legacy-memory-quarantine/15-03-26_12-27__i-m-starting-with-the-repo-s-own-runbook-and.md:616:**Selected**: The template frontmatter trigger_phrases field now uses the  system spec kit/022 hybrid rag fusion/010 perfect session capturing, dry run, rejection code, no data available, memory_save, render quality, re reading, m 007, json mode, repo local, save path, target spec, tool call, current spec, auto fixes, warn only, save quality, under evidenced, hard blocks, post render, home directory, negative path, user selected, tree thinning, implementation summary, malformed generated memory files, system, spec, kit/022, hybrid, rag, fusion/010, perfect, session, capturing mustache variable instead of hardcoded strings.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:4287:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/scratch/legacy-memory-quarantine/15-03-26_12-27__i-m-starting-with-the-repo-s-own-runbook-and.md:1177:Analyze this issue spotted by plan Plan: Fix Memory File Generation Quality (Root Cause) Spec folder:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing Context Generated memory files (output of generate-context.js) have systemic quality issues: missing ANCHOR tags, generic frontmatter trigger phrases, and cross-session contamination. The user's most recent memory save produced an 893-line file with zero ANCHOR tags despite the template containing 26 of them, and frontmatter trigger_phrases that say "memory dashboard" / "session summary" instead of session-specific content. Additionally, when saving from Claude Code (or any external CLI), the script's session capture detects the active OpenCode editor session instead of the calling session, leading to ALIGNMENT_BLOCK rejections or saving the wrong session's context. Root cause investigation traced these to bugs in scripts/core/workflow.ts and templates/context_template.md. --- Root Cause Analysis BUG 1: ANCHOR tags destroyed by HTML comment stripping (CRITICAL) Location: workflow.ts:108,162-179,1360-1364 Chain of events: 1. Template context_template.md contains 26 ANCHOR tags: &lt;!-- ANCHOR:id --&gt; / &lt;!-- /ANCHOR:id --&gt; 2. Step 8 (populateTemplate) renders the template correctly, anchors intact 3. Step 8.5 calls stripWorkflowHtmlOutsideCodeFences() on the rendered output 4. That function uses WORKFLOW_HTML_COMMENT_RE = //g (line 108) 5. This regex matches all HTML comments, including every ANCHOR tag 6. Line 171:.replace(WORKFLOW_HTML_COMMENT_RE, '') — deletes them all 7. Result: 0 ANCHOR tags in output file Irony: Line 538 has extractAnchorIds() that parses ANCHOR tags — but it runs after they've been destroyed. Fix: Modify the HTML comment regex to exclude ANCHOR comments: // Before (line 108): const WORKFLOW_HTML_COMMENT_RE = //g; // After: const WORKFLOW_HTML_COMMENT_RE = //g; The negative lookahead (?!\s*\/?ANCHOR:) preserves &lt;!-- ANCHOR:id --&gt; and &lt;!-- /ANCHOR:id --&gt; while still stripping all other HTML comments. BUG 2: Frontmatter trigger_phrases are hardcoded (HIGH) Location: templates/context_template.md:4-7 vs templates/context_template.md:807-811 Chain of events: 1. Template frontmatter (lines 4-7) has static values: trigger_phrases: - "memory dashboard" - "session summary" - "context template" 2. The  system spec kit/022 hybrid rag fusion/010 perfect session capturing, dry run, rejection code, no data available, memory_save, render quality, re reading, m 007, json mode, repo local, save path, target spec, tool call, current spec, auto fixes, warn only, save quality, under evidenced, hard blocks, post render, home directory, negative path, user selected, tree thinning, implementation summary, malformed generated memory files, system, spec, kit/022, hybrid, rag, fusion/010, perfect, session, capturing mustache variable IS used — but only in the YAML metadata block at line 807-811 (inside the trailing ```yaml code fence) 3. The workflow DOES extract session-specific triggers (preExtractedTriggers, line 1231-1269) and passes them as TRIGGER_PHRASES to the template (line 1315) 4. But the frontmatter section never references  system spec kit/022 hybrid rag fusion/010 perfect session capturing, dry run, rejection code, no data available, memory_save, render quality, re reading, m 007, json mode, repo local, save path, target spec, tool call, current spec, auto fixes, warn only, save quality, under evidenced, hard blocks, post render, home directory, negative path, user selected, tree thinning, implementation summary, malformed generated memory files, system, spec, kit/022, hybrid, rag, fusion/010, perfect, session, capturing — it uses hardcoded strings Fix: Replace the static frontmatter trigger_phrases with the template variable: # Before (lines 4-7): trigger_phrases: - "memory dashboard" - "session summary" - "context template" # After: trigger_phrases: {{#TRIGGER_PHRASES}} - "" {{/TRIGGER_PHRASES}}  BUG 3: Cross-session contamination in direct-path mode (HIGH) Location: workflow.ts — collectSessionData() call path in direct-path mode Chain of events: 1. User runs generate-context.js specs/015-skill-alignment from Claude Code CLI 2. The script's direct-path mode calls collectSessionData() which captures the active OpenCode editor session (e.g., "Media Editor: Convert images to webp") 3. The alignment check compares this unrelated session against the target spec folder 4. Result: 0 file matches, 0 phrase matches → ALIGNMENT_BLOCK error 5. Workaround: user must fall back to JSON file mode (/tmp/save-context-data.json) The JSON fallback produces lower quality because it lacks the rich session data (file diffs, observations, tool calls) that automatic capture provides. This creates a two-tier quality problem: sessions saved from external CLIs are always worse. Fix: When JSON data is provided (Mode 1), skip collectSessionData() entirely — the caller has already provided the session context. The alignment check should only run when using direct-path mode (Mode 2) with auto-captured session data. --- Files to Modify ┌─────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────┐ │ # │ File │ Change │ ├─────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────┤ │ │ │ Fix HTML comment │ │ 1 │.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/core/workflow.ts │ regex to preserve │ │ │ │ ANCHOR tags (line │ │ │ │ 108) │ ├─────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────┤ │ │ │ Replace hardcoded │ │ 2 │.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/context_template.md │ frontmatter │ │ │ │ trigger_phrases with │ │ │ │  system spec kit/022 hybrid rag fusion/010 perfect session capturing, dry run, rejection code, no data available, memory_save, render quality, re reading, m 007, json mode, repo local, save path, target spec, tool call, current spec, auto fixes, warn only, save quality, under evidenced, hard blocks, post render, home directory, negative path, user selected, tree thinning, implementation summary, malformed generated memory files, system, spec, kit/022, hybrid, rag, fusion/010, perfect, session, capturing │ ├─────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────┤ │ │ │ Skip session capture │ │ 3 │.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/core/workflow.ts │ when JSON data is │ │ │ │ provided (Bug 3) │ └─────┴───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────┘ --- Verification 1. ANCHOR preservation: Run generate-context.js on a spec folder and grep output for ANCHOR: grep -c 'ANCHOR' <output-file>.md # Should be >0 (expect ~26 pairs) 2. Trigger phrase replacement: Check frontmatter of generated file: head -10 <output-file>.md # Should NOT contain "memory dashboard", "session summary", "context template" # Should contain session-specific phrases 3. HTML stripping still works: Verify non-ANCHOR HTML comments are still stripped: grep -c '<!-- Template Configuration' <output-file>.md # Should be 0 (template config comments still stripped) 4. Existing tests pass: cd.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit && npm run test --workspace=scripts 5. Quality score impact: The quality scorer at line 1434 checks html (noLeakedTags). Verify the ANCHOR preservation doesn't trigger false positives — ANCHOR tags are valid markdown comments, not "leaked HTML". | Use same spec folder /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode Env/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:4288:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/scratch/legacy-memory-quarantine/15-03-26_12-27__i-m-starting-with-the-repo-s-own-runbook-and.md:1183:PLEASE IMPLEMENT THIS PLAN: # Fix Memory File Generation Quality in `009-perfect-session-capturing` ## Summary Implement the two confirmed rendering fixes as stated, and correct the third fix so it addresses the real bug. - `BUG 1` is real: anchor comments are stripped after template rendering. Fix the workflow HTML-comment stripper so it preserves only `&lt;!-- ANCHOR:* --&gt;` and `&lt;!-- /ANCHOR:* --&gt;`, while still removing all other workflow/template comments. - `BUG 2` is real: frontmatter `trigger_phrases` is static while the workflow already computes dynamic phrases. Replace the hardcoded frontmatter values with the same dynamic trigger rendering used later in the file, and make the no-trigger fallback empty rather than generic placeholder phrases. - `BUG 3` is a diagnosis correction: explicit JSON mode already bypasses native session capture. The real problem is direct-path mode choosing the wrong native backend because loader precedence ignores the calling CLI. Do not skip `collectSessionData()` for JSON mode; instead make native capture selection caller-aware in direct mode. ## Key Changes ### 1. Preserve anchor tags in rendered memory files - Update the HTML comment stripping logic in [`workflow.ts`](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/core/workflow.ts) so only non-anchor HTML comments are removed. - Preserve both opening and closing anchor comments exactly as rendered by the template. - Keep the existing post-render cleanup behavior for template configuration comments and other non-anchor comments. - Add a regression around the cleaning step itself, not just end-to-end output, so future regex changes cannot silently erase anchors again. ### 2. Make frontmatter trigger phrases session-specific - Update [`context_template.md`](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/context_template.md) so frontmatter `trigger_phrases` uses the computed `TRIGGER_PHRASES` variable instead of hardcoded strings. - Use the same behavior in both places where trigger phrases appear in the template so frontmatter and trailing metadata cannot drift apart. - If no triggers are extracted, render an empty list instead of generic phrases like `"memory dashboard"` or `"session summary"`. ### 3. Fix direct-path cross-session contamination at backend selection - Keep explicit JSON mode unchanged: file input remains authoritative and must never consult native capture fallbacks. - Add an internal native-capture preference hint for direct-path mode, derived in this order: 1. explicit env override such as `SYSTEM_SPEC_KIT_CAPTURE_SOURCE` 2. inferred runtime markers for known CLIs 3. existing default fallback order if no hint is available - Pass that preferred source into native loading so the caller’s backend is tried first, then the remaining backends in the existing order. - If the preferred backend has no usable session, continue falling back normally. - Do not weaken alignment, contamination, or sufficiency gates. This change only fixes which session source is chosen first. ### 4. Keep quality gates aligned with the fix - Verify that preserved anchor comments do not trip leaked-HTML or formatting checks in the render/quality pipeline. - Keep trigger extraction and frontmatter metadata consistent with the actual saved session so memory files stop looking generic even when the body is correct. - Update the spec folder docs in `009-perfect-session-capturing` so the root cause and fix for direct-path contamination explicitly describe caller-aware backend preference, not “skip `collectSessionData()` in JSON mode.” ## Public Interfaces / Types - No user-facing CLI signature change for `generate-context.js`. - Add one internal native-capture preference field that can flow from CLI/runtime detection into the loader, for example `preferredCaptureSource`. - Add one documented env override for external CLIs: - `SYSTEM_SPEC_KIT_CAPTURE_SOURCE=opencode|claude|codex|copilot|gemini` - JSON file mode remains authoritative and unchanged. - `collectSessionData()` behavior remains unchanged; the fix is in source selection, not post-load session assembly. ## Test Plan 1. Rendering regressions - Template render preserves anchor comments after cleanup. - Non-anchor workflow/template comments are still stripped. - Rendered output contains anchor pairs and does not contain stripped configuration comments. - Anchor comments do not trigger leaked-HTML quality failures. 2. Trigger phrase regressions - Frontmatter contains session-specific trigger phrases when extracted. - Frontmatter no longer contains `"memory dashboard"`, `"session summary"`, or `"context template"`. - No-trigger case renders an empty trigger list, not generic placeholders. - Frontmatter trigger phrases and trailing metadata trigger phrases stay in sync. 3. Native capture selection regressions - Explicit JSON mode never invokes native capture and keeps current behavior. - Direct mode with `SYSTEM_SPEC_KIT_CAPTURE_SOURCE=claude` prefers Claude over OpenCode when both sessions exist. - Equivalent coverage for `codex`, `copilot`, and `gemini`. - If the preferred backend returns no usable session, fallback continues in the current default order. - If no hint is available, current default order remains unchanged. 4. End-to-end verification - Generate a memory file and confirm anchors are present, frontmatter triggers are session-specific, and template comments are stripped. - Re-run the targeted scripts test suites that cover runtime inputs, CLI authority, rendering, and loader behavior. - Re-run the repo verification stack already used for `010`: lint, build, targeted Vitest, JS regression suites, alignment drift, and spec validation. ## Assumptions And Defaults - The user’s spec folder remains [`009-perfect-session-capturing`](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing). - The correct fix for external-CLI contamination is caller-aware native backend preference, not changing JSON-mode post-processing. - When no caller-specific trigger phrases exist, empty metadata is preferable to misleading generic placeholders. - External CLI wrappers should set `SYSTEM_SPEC_KIT_CAPTURE_SOURCE` when possible; runtime inference is only a fallback, not the primary contract.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:4289:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/scratch/legacy-memory-quarantine/15-03-26_12-27__i-m-starting-with-the-repo-s-own-runbook-and.md:1303:PLEASE IMPLEMENT THIS PLAN: # Fix Rendered Memory Quality and Re-close `009-perfect-session-capturing` ## Summary Use Claude’s results as the baseline truth: the backend wiring, anchor-preserving regex, sufficiency hook, and most automated coverage are already in place, but live manual behavior is still broken by a render-layer regression and a JSON contract mismatch. The implementation should fix those root causes, then do a broader cleanup of malformed generated memory files under the `010` spec’s `memory/` folder and rerun the canonical verification pack so the spec folder is validation-clean again. ## Key Changes ### 1. Fix `trigger_phrases` rendering at the template layer - Replace the nested identical `{{#TRIGGER_PHRASES}}` blocks in `context_template.md` with a render shape that cannot leak raw Mustache tags. - Render exactly one `trigger_phrases:` header followed by a YAML list when phrases exist, and `trigger_phrases: []` when they do not. - Apply the same fix to both the frontmatter block and the trailing metadata block so they stay identical. - Preserve the existing ANCHOR-preserving cleanup behavior; only non-anchor HTML comments should still be stripped. ### 2. Make JSON-mode input accept the documented contract - Update normalization so JSON mode accepts both the documented snake_case keys and the existing camelCase keys for the save surface: - `user_prompts` / `userPrompts` - `recent_context` / `recentContext` - `trigger_phrases` / `triggerPhrases` - any other paired fields already implied by docs/tests - Keep explicit JSON mode authoritative and bypass native session capture exactly as it does now. - Treat the CLI help text as the compatibility contract: after the fix, the documented snake_case example must work end to end without dropping messages. ### 3. Make thin saves fail explicitly before write - Tighten the save path so thin aligned JSON and thin native captures hard-stop with `INSUFFICIENT_CONTEXT_ABORT` before file write and indexing, not “write a file + skip indexing on `V7`”. - Keep failure boundaries explicit: - off-spec same-workspace capture: `ALIGNMENT_BLOCK` - foreign-spec-dominated or malformed semantic content: existing quality/contamination path - not enough durable evidence: `INSUFFICIENT_CONTEXT_ABORT` - Ensure sufficiency evaluation runs early enough that obviously under-evidenced saves cannot produce repo-tracked memory files. ### 4. Reconcile validator behavior with the fixed output - Confirm the fixed `trigger_phrases` render no longer causes `V5`. - Confirm preserved ANCHOR comments do not trigger leaked-HTML or placeholder checks. - If the validator currently assumes only parsed YAML lists and misses valid rendered phrases, update it only as needed to accept the corrected output, not to tolerate malformed output. ### 5. Clean the `010` spec memory folder and refresh docs/evidence - Perform the user-selected broader cleanup of malformed generated memory files under `009-perfect-session-capturing/memory/`. - Regenerate only canonical evidence artifacts needed for the spec after the code fixes. - Update the `010` spec docs and manual playbook so they reflect the actual fixed behavior: - dynamic trigger phrases render correctly - JSON mode accepts the documented input shape - thin saves abort before write - direct-mode caller preference remains the right fix for cross-session contamination - Refresh spec validation evidence so the folder passes without warnings caused by stale malformed memory files. ## Interfaces / Contracts - No CLI signature change for `generate-context.js`. - Preserve `SYSTEM_SPEC_KIT_CAPTURE_SOURCE` behavior. - Expand JSON input compatibility so documented snake_case and existing camelCase both work. - Keep the stable explicit failure code `INSUFFICIENT_CONTEXT_ABORT`; this is the expected outcome for thin aligned saves across JSON and native capture. ## Test Plan - Template/render regressions: - rendered output contains ANCHOR comments after cleanup - non-anchor template comments are stripped - frontmatter `trigger_phrases` is a valid YAML list or `[]` - trailing metadata `trigger_phrases` matches the same behavior - no raw `{{#TRIGGER_PHRASES}}` or repeated `trigger_phrases:` headers leak into output - JSON contract regressions: - rich snake_case JSON fixture passes the same way as camelCase - thin snake_case JSON fixture triggers `INSUFFICIENT_CONTEXT_ABORT` - explicit JSON mode still does not invoke native capture - Save-path/sufficiency regressions: - thin aligned JSON aborts before file write and before indexing - same-workspace off-spec OpenCode capture still `ALIGNMENT_BLOCK`s - backend-specific direct-mode runs no longer fail `V5` due to malformed trigger rendering - Full verification rerun: - targeted scripts Vitest suite - JS regression suites - MCP save-quality tests impacted by sufficiency - alignment drift - `spec/validate.sh` for `010` - Manual rerun of `M-007`: - `M-007a` rich JSON writes cleanly, preserves anchors, uses valid session-specific trigger phrases, and indexes - `M-007b` thin JSON hard-fails `INSUFFICIENT_CONTEXT_ABORT` with no memory file written - `M-007c` OpenCode same-workspace off-spec run still `ALIGNMENT_BLOCK`s - `M-007f` to `M-007i` verify backend selection plus post-fix save behavior without `V5` render corruption - `M-007j` still returns `NO_DATA_AVAILABLE` ## Assumptions and Defaults - Claude’s automated results are directionally correct; the plan treats the render bug and JSON contract drift as the real blockers to trustable manual verification. - The documented CLI JSON format is the source of truth, so implementation should add compatibility rather than rewrite docs to camelCase-only behavior. - Broader cleanup of malformed generated memory files under the `010` spec is authorized and should be completed as part of the fix so validation/manual evidence is not polluted by stale artifacts. - The goal is a truly clean close: fixed generator behavior, fixed manual scenarios, and a warning-free `010` spec folder.
