.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/gpt55/iterations/iteration-003.md:4296:.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing/scratch/legacy-memory-quarantine/15-03-26_12-25__how-is-used-later-in-the-template-to-match-th.md:649:Implement the following plan: # Plan: Fix Memory File Generation Quality (Root Cause) **Spec folder:** `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/009-perfect-session-capturing` ## Context Generated memory files (output of `generate-context.js`) have systemic quality issues: missing ANCHOR tags, generic frontmatter trigger phrases, and cross-session contamination. The user's most recent memory save produced an 893-line file with zero ANCHOR tags despite the template containing 26 of them, and frontmatter trigger_phrases that say "memory dashboard" / "session summary" instead of session-specific content. Additionally, when saving from Claude Code (or any external CLI), the script's session capture detects the active OpenCode editor session instead of the calling session, leading to ALIGNMENT_BLOCK rejections or saving the wrong session's context. Root cause investigation traced these to bugs in `scripts/core/workflow.ts` and `templates/context_template.md`. --- ## Root Cause Analysis ### BUG 1: ANCHOR tags destroyed by HTML comment stripping (CRITICAL) **Location:** `workflow.ts:108,162-179,1360-1364` **Chain of events:** 1. Templ/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2024:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/010-references-assets-lane-reorg/implementation-summary.md:12:    packet_pointer: "skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/010-references-assets-lane-reorg"
