.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49032:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2065:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/019-skill-doc-alignment-and-changelog-consolidation/implementation-summary.md:51:The deep-agent-improvement skill's docs now tell the truth about what packet 121 built. The changelog is one comprehensive v1.9.0.0 entry covering the whole program, and the README presents the skill as the two-lane tool it became instead of the pre-121 single-lane one.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49033:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2066:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/019-skill-doc-alignment-and-changelog-consolidation/implementation-summary.md:55:`changelog/v1.9.0.0.md` now covers all 18 phases of packet 121 across both arcs: building the model-benchmark mode (001-007) and elevating it into a co-equal lane (008-018), including both deep-review and remediation cycles. It previously captured only phases 008-013. The version stays 1.9.0.0, and packet 116's `v1.8.0.0.md` is left untouched.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49034:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2067:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/019-skill-doc-alignment-and-changelog-consolidation/implementation-summary.md:59:The README STRUCTURE tree now shows the real lane subdirs (`agent-improvement/`, `model-benchmark/`, `shared/`) instead of the pre-121 function grouping. A new "Two Lanes" section names Lane B and the `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` command, the reference and script counts match the on-disk tree (14 references, 16 scripts), and the model-benchmark entry-point scripts (`loop-host.cjs`, `dispatch-model.cjs`, the `scorer/` subtree) are now in the scripts table.
