.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49253:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2286:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/011-agent-lane-note/plan.md:51:Replace the single "Mode awareness" note in the canonical agent file with a "Lane awareness" note that frames the skill as two co-equal lanes and clarifies Lane B dispatches MODELS through one agent only. Copy that prose byte-identical into the .claude and .gemini markdown mirrors and into the .codex TOML developer_instructions string.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49265:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2298:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:28:# Decision Record: Design: add a model/prompt-framework benchmark mode to deep-agent-improvement (port the 120/003 rig behind a mode selector)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49268:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2301:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:54:The 120/003 packet proved a model/prompt-framework benchmark loop works (run MiniMax against fixtures under 5 frameworks, score, hill-climb, pick TIDD-EC + dense). But that rig is packet-local and one-off. deep-agent-improvement runs the same loop shape (generate candidate, score, converge, promote) for agent definitions. We needed to decide how to make model benchmarking a reusable capability without duplicating loop infrastructure or distorting the existing agent-improvement skill.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49270:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2303:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:69:**We chose**: Add a `mode` config key to deep-agent-improvement with two values, `agent-improvement` (default, today's behavior) and `model-benchmark` (port of the 120/003 rig), dispatched through three pluggable seams.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49273:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2306:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:77:| Candidate source | parse `.opencode/agents/*.md` into a scored candidate | render a prompt-framework variant (port `render-variant.cjs` + variant templates from 120/003) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49282:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2315:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:113:- ~90% of the loop infra is shared, so the new mode is mostly seams + a ported scorer, not a second engine.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49285:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2318:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:134:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | We just hand-ported the rig for 120/003; the next model benchmark would repeat that. |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49287:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2320:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:136:| 3 | **Sufficient?** | PASS | Mode selector + 3 seams is the minimum that reuses the plumbing without unifying the incompatible scorers. |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49291:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2324:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:150:- New `dispatch-model.cjs` + ported `eval-rig/` + `score-variant.cjs`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49292:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2325:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/decision-record.md:159:## ADR-002: deep-agent-improvement is the home (not a new skill, not deep-loop-runtime)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49298:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2331:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:3:description: "Architecture decisions and per-finding disposition register for remediating the 014 two-lane deep review: space-form parser, read-only grader sandbox, fixture-id sanitization, criteria-exec fail-closed default, packet-local candidate-keyed cache."
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49299:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2332:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:7:  - "Lane B parser decision"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49300:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2333:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:12:    packet_pointer: "skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49301:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2334:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:32:<!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr_rules.md -->
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49302:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2335:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:52:The 014 review confirmed F-P0-1: `loop-host.cjs` `parseArgs` only accepts `--key=value` and bare flags, but all three Lane B command surfaces invoke loop-host with SPACE-form flags (`--profile {profile} --scorer {scoring_method} --grader {grader}`), so `profile`, `outputs-dir`, `scorer`, and `grader` all parse to `true`. The model-benchmark command does not run as intended. We could either teach the parser the space-form or rewrite the three command surfaces to `=`-form.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49303:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2336:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:56:- TST-1 byte-identity gate must hold: the `=`-form parse path and the Lane A plan must be byte-identical pre and post fix.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49304:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2337:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:89:- The Lane B command runs as intended through the YAML path.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49305:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2338:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:110:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | P0 release blocker; Lane B is broken without it |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49306:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2339:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:125:- `scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs` `parseArgs`: additive space-form branch.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49307:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2340:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:126:- `scripts/tests/loop-host.vitest.ts`: space-form test + TST-1 identity assertion.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49308:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2341:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:150:F-P1-1 found `buildSpawnSpec` runs external model executors with write-capable modes (Claude `--permission-mode acceptEdits`, Codex `--sandbox workspace-write`, Devin `--permission-mode auto`). Grading and benchmarking should observe output, not edit the workspace.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49309:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2342:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:163:**We chose**: Default grader/executor dispatch to read-only/no-edit modes, with an explicit documented opt-in for write-capable evaluation in an isolated temp workspace, and assert `cwd` stays inside the benchmark sandbox before spawning.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49310:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2343:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:165:**How it works**: `buildSpawnSpec` emits read-only permission flags per executor by default. A documented opt-in flag or env var switches to write-capable mode only when the caller explicitly requests it, and the spawn path validates the resolved `cwd` is inside the benchmark sandbox first.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49311:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2344:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:222:- `scripts/model-benchmark/dispatch-model.cjs` `buildSpawnSpec`: read-only default + cwd sandbox assert + opt-in.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49312:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2345:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:247:F-P1-9 found fixture-controlled `fixture.id` is used in `path.join(outputsDir, ` + "`${fixture.id}.md`" + `)` without validating it is a basename or that the resolved path stays under `outputsDir`. A crafted id with separators or `..` can read or score files outside the benchmark output directory.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49313:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2346:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:262:**How it works**: A small guard validates the id is a single safe basename, the runner resolves `outputsDir` and the candidate path, and asserts containment via a separator-bounded prefix check before any file access.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49314:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2347:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:284:- Fixture ids cannot escape the benchmark output directory.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49315:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2348:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:318:- `scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs`: fixture-id guard + resolved-inside-outputs assert.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49316:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2349:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:347:- Existing trusted benchmark profiles may rely on criteria execution and must remain reachable via explicit opt-in.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49317:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2350:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:424:## ADR-005: Move the score cache packet-local and key it by candidate
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49318:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2351:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:439:Two findings target the score cache. F-P1-11: `defaultCacheDir()` stores scores under `os.tmpdir()/deep-agent-improvement-score-cache`, a shared world-writable path that is later trusted before rescoring. F-P1-12: the cache input hash includes candidate content and target path but not `candidatePath` or `baselinePath`, so a cache hit can carry the wrong candidate or baseline path in the result payload.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49319:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2352:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:444:- Cache hits must not mislabel which candidate or baseline produced the score.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49320:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2353:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:452:**We chose**: Store the cache packet-local (under the runtime/packet root) with owner/mode validation, treat unreadable or untrusted entries as cache misses, and include `candidatePath` and `baselinePath` in the cache key.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49321:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2354:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:454:**How it works**: `defaultCacheDir()` resolves under the packet/runtime root with restrictive permissions; reads validate owner and mode and fall back to a miss on mismatch. The cache key hash adds the candidate and baseline paths, so a hit always corresponds to the exact candidate it scored.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49322:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2355:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:464:| **Packet-local + candidate-keyed (chosen)** | Closes the trust gap and the mislabel gap together | Cache no longer shared across packets | 9/10 |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49323:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2356:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:477:- A cache hit always names the correct candidate and baseline.
