.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49492:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2525:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/spec.md:29:# Feature Specification: Design: add a model/prompt-framework benchmark mode to deep-agent-improvement (port the 120/003 rig behind a mode selector)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49493:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2526:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/spec.md:54:The 120/003 packet built a working model/prompt-framework benchmark rig (run a model against fixtures under different prompt variants, score, hill-climb to a winner) but it lives packet-local and one-off. `deep-agent-improvement` already runs the same shape of loop (generate candidate, score, converge, promote) for agent definitions. This design adds a **mode selector** to deep-agent-improvement so it can run BOTH `agent-improvement` (today) and a new `model-benchmark` mode (port of the 120/003 rig), reusing ~90% of the shared loop/state/convergence/mutation plumbing and plugging in mode-specific candidate-source, dispatcher, and scorer.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49494:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2527:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/spec.md:56:**Key Decisions**: mode selector (not a separate skill); deep-agent-improvement is the home (not deep-loop-runtime, which is a read-only library); pluggable seams keep the two modes' scorers/promotion separate.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49495:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2528:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/spec.md:58:**Critical Dependencies**: the 120/003 rig (`eval-rig` + `eval-loop/scripts`) as the portable source; deep-agent-improvement's existing generic scripts (`mutation-coverage.cjs`, `reduce-state.cjs`, `converge.cjs`, `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs`, `improvement-journal.cjs`).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49496:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2529:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/spec.md:73:| **Predecessor** | `skilled-agent-orchestration/120-cli-opencode-minimax-optimization/003-minimax-prompt-framework-benchmark` (the rig this generalizes) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49497:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2530:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/spec.md:83:We now have two near-identical evaluation loops: `deep-agent-improvement` (mutate + score an agent definition, promote the best) and the 120/003 benchmark rig (run a model against fixtures under prompt-framework variants, score, pick the best). The benchmark rig is packet-local and not reusable, so every future "find the best framework/config for model X" effort would re-port it by hand. There is no first-class, repeatable way to benchmark a model/prompt across the toolchain.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49498:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2531:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/spec.md:86:deep-agent-improvement can run a `model-benchmark` mode (real model dispatch + fixture scoring + hill-climbing to a winning prompt/config) alongside its existing `agent-improvement` mode, so model/prompt benchmarking is a standard, repeatable capability rather than a one-off rig.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49499:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2532:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/spec.md:95:- A complete design + decision-record for the mode selector and the three pluggable seams (candidate source, dispatcher, scorer)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49500:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2533:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/spec.md:96:- A reuse map (which 120/003 + deep-agent-improvement scripts port as-is vs need generalizing) and a build sequence + effort estimate in plan.md/tasks.md
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49501:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-001.out:2534:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/001-mode-selector-design/spec.md:101:- A separate new skill - the capability lands inside deep-agent-improvement, not a new skill or deep-loop-runtime (which is a read-only library)
