.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49675:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/graph-metadata.json:207:    "causal_summary": "This is **Phase 8** of the two-lane program. The deep-agent-improvement skill already has two runtime lanes: Lane A (agent-improvement, improve an agent `.md` file) and Lane B (model-benchmark, benchmark or optimize a model or prompt framework). Lane B works as a skill mode but has no command entry. This phase makes Lane B first-class at the command layer.",
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:49676:-.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/005-optin-5dim-scorer-and-skill-docs/spec.md:3:description: "Phase 5 of 121: wire the ported 120/003 5-dimension scorer as an opt-in run-benchmark scorer (closing review deferral F-P2-1/F-P2-2) and align/document the deep-agent-improvement skill docs against sk-doc templates."
