.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:50132:-.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md:88:No systematic way to evaluate agent prompt files. Manual review was inconsistent and could not track improvement over time. Created `sk-deep-agent-improvement` with 8 scripts: `scan-integration.cjs` discovers all surfaces an agent touches (main, mirrors, commands, YAML, skills); `generate-profile.cjs` derives scoring from any agent's own rules; `score-candidate.cjs` scores across 5 weighted dimensions (structural 0.20, ruleCoherence 0.25, integration 0.25, outputQuality 0.15, systemFitness 0.15). All scoring is deterministic -- regex, string matching, file-existence checks -- no LLM-as-judge.
