.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:50352:-.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/003-memory-and-causal-runtime/003-embedder-testing-and-architecture/004-code-index-stack/011-rerank-model-fit-investigation/research/phase2-bench/jina-v3.rerank-scores.jsonl:9:{"query": "Framework: RCAF # 016/004/013 \u2014 Bench Harness Hardening + Full Fixture Audit (production-quality, future-proof) Apply sequential_thinking with >= 5 thoughts BEFORE making any edit. ## Pre-planning **Sequential_thinking mandatory**: call mcp__sequential_thinking__sequentialthinking with >= 5 thoughts covering: (1) read spec.md fully + the two bench harness scripts + the fixture, (2) plan the path-extraction helper structure + test coverage, (3) plan the fixture audit sqlite query approach, (4) plan re-bench invocation + corrected output paths, (5) plan ADR + README updates and the strict-validate pass. **Role**: You are the implementation owner for packet 016/004/013 in a 6-packet future-proofing arc on the CocoIndex retrieval pipeline. The operator's stated principles: (a) fix code, don't bandaid with model swaps, (b) wide embedder support, best perf in all situations, (c) prioritize future-proof + hardened + strong + effective solutions over speed. This packet is the MEASUREMENT-QUALITY PREREQUISITE for the 5 downstream packets \u2014 every other packet's bench result is only trustworthy after this lands. Gate 3 PRE-ANSWERED: spec folder = `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/013-embedder-testing-and-architecture/004-code-index-stack/013-bench-harness-and-fixture-audit/`. All writes confined to that folder, the two bench harness scripts, the fixture file, and the bake-off decision record (for ADR-016). **Context** (read FIRST before any edit): - Spec contract: `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/013-embedder-testing-and-architecture/004-code-index-stack/013-bench-harness-and-fixture-audit/spec.md` \u2014 the full \u00a73 SCOPE + \u00a74 REQUIREMENTS list. Implement per spec; if a requirement is ambiguous, document the interpretation in implementation-summary.md. - Two harness scripts: - `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/013-embedder-testing-and-architecture/004-code-index-stack/011-rerank-model-fit-investigation/research/phase2-bench/run-phase2-smoke.sh` - `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/013-embedder-testing-and-architecture/004-code-index-stack/004-extended-bake-off/evidence/run-extended-bake-off-with-hybrid-rerank.sh` - Fixture: `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/013-embedder-testing-and-architecture/004-code-index-stack/002-baseline-fixture/evidence/code-retrieval-fixture.json` (18 probes) - Live DB for audit queries: `.cocoindex_code/target_sqlite.db` (628 MB, bge-code-v1 indexed); use the project venv's sqlite3 module \u2014 `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/.venv/bin/python` is the canonical Python - Phase 2 bench artifacts (read-only \u2014 these are the inputs we're correcting): `phase2-bench/baseline-bge.results.jsonl`, `phase2-bench/jina-v3.results.jsonl`, `phase2-bench/phase2-comparison.md` - Project exclusion settings: `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/cocoindex_code/settings.py` + `.cocoindex_code/settings.yml` - Earlier deep-research evidence cited in spec.md \u00a72 PROBLEM: - Iter 5 of `011-rerank-model-fit-investigation/research/cocoindex-internals-deep-dive/iterations/iteration-005.md` proved probe 10's `.js` dist isn't indexed (0 vec rows, 0 FTS rows) - Iter 5 also documented the backtick path-extraction defect on probe 11 **Goal**: Implement R1-R10 from spec.md \u00a74. Hardened harness + audited fixture + corrected fixture + re-bench output + ADR + README + pytest coverage. Strict-validate PASSED. ## Steps (medium-density pre-planning, 4 ordered) 1. **Phase 1 \u2014 path-extraction hardening (~45 min).** - Refactor the Python heredoc in `run-phase2-smoke.sh` to use a named helper `_extract_paths(stdout: str) -> list[str]`. The helper: - Splits on lines - For each token containing `/` and `.`: - Strip leading/trailing backticks, single quotes, double quotes - Strip `import('...')` / `require('...')` / `from '...'` / `from \"...\"` wrappers (extract the inner path) - Strip line-range suffixes (`:N-M`, `:N`) - Strip trailing punctuation - Apply mirror-prefix awareness: if token starts with `.opencode/`, `.claude/`, `.codex/`, `.gemini/`, keep it - Filesystem-existence sanity check: if token doesn't match mirror-prefix AND doesn't resolve to a real file, discard it (this filters `'./measurement-fixtures.js'`-style mock literals) - Return deduplicated list preserving rank order - Apply identical helper to `run-extended-bake-off-with-hybrid-rerank.sh` (the Python heredoc inside the bash script). - Acceptance: both scripts have the helper, output schema unchanged (same JSONL + CSV columns). - Verification: pytest module at `013-bench-harness-and-fixture-audit/scratch/test_path_extraction.py` with \u22656 tests covering wrapper patterns + edge cases. All pass under `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/.venv/bin/python -m pytest`. 2. **Phase 2 \u2014 full fixture audit (~30 min).** - For each probe in the 18-probe fixture: query the live `target_sqlite.db` using read-only sqlite3 attach. Sample query: `SELECT COUNT(*) FROM code_chunks_vec JOIN code_chunks USING(chunk_id) WHERE file_path LIKE '%<probe_expected_filename>%'`. Inspect the schema first to confirm table/column names. - Classify each probe as `indexed` / `excluded` / `missing` with `_audit_evidence` field (the COUNT result + sample chunk_id). - For `excluded` probes: read `cocoindex_code/settings.py` + `.cocoindex_code/settings.yml` to identify the exclusion reason (which glob pattern excluded it). Record in `_audit_evidence`. - Emit `phase2-bench/code-retrieval-fixture-audited.json` (the annotated 18-probe fixture with status per probe). - Acceptance: every probe has `_fixture_status` + `_audit_evidence` fields. - Verification: probe 10 specifically must show `_fixture_status: excluded` with rationale citing the `**/dist` exclusion pattern. 3. **Phase 3 \u2014 corrected fixture + re-bench (~30 min).** - Emit `phase2-bench/code-retrieval-fixture-corrected.json` derived from the audited fixture. For each `excluded` probe, either (a) re-point `expected_source_path` to an indexed alternative (e.g. probe 10 \u2192 `.ts` source `scripts/memory/generate-context.ts` since that file is indexed) AND add `_corrected_from` field documenting the change, OR (b) mark `_skip: true` with rationale. - Run `run-phase2-smoke.sh` against the corrected fixture: `FIXTURE_OVERRIDE=phase2-bench/code-retrieval-fixture-corrected.json bash phase2-bench/run-phase2-smoke.sh`. This produces a new comparison report. - Move the new comparison to `phase2-bench/phase2-comparison-corrected.md`. Also write `phase2-bench/phase2-comparison-baseline-vs-corrected-delta.md` showing which probes flipped due to (harness fix only) vs (fixture fix only) vs (both). - Acceptance: corrected bench shows \u22651 probe flipped from miss \u2192 hit due to harness fix (the backtick recovery cases). Probe 10 either flips to hit (under re-pointed target) or is documented as skip. 4. **Phase 4 \u2014 ADR + README + strict-validate + commit handoff (~15 min).** - Append `ADR-016: Bench harness hardening + fixture audit` to `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/013-embedder-testing-and-architecture/002-spec-memory-stack/004-spec-memory-embedder-bake-off/decision-record.md`. Cover: defects found (path-extraction false-misses + probe 10 excluded), fixes applied, new measurement contract (downstream 014-018 compare against `phase2-comparison-corrected.md`), rollback path. - Update `phase2-bench/README.md` to reference the corrected fixture as canonical + cross-link the audit + delta artifacts. - Write canonical L1 `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `implementation-summary.md` (the spec.md already exists). Fill `implementation-summary.md` \u00a7\"Files Changed\" + \u00a7\"Commit Handoff\" with explicit path list. - Run `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/013-embedder-testing-and-architecture/004-code-index-stack/013-bench-harness-and-fixture-audit --strict`. Iterate fixes until PASSED. ## Research Question (scoped) How do we harden bench measurement quality so that downstream packets 014-018 (mirror dedup, tree-sitter chunking, query expansion, hybrid recalib, rerank matrix re-bench) can be evaluated against a trustworthy baseline? ## Output contract Primary deliverables in the packet folder: - `spec.md` (already exists \u2014 do NOT rewrite, only patch if frontmatter needs continuity update) - `plan.md` (NEW \u2014 canonical L1 template) - `tasks.md` (NEW \u2014 canonical L1 template, mark all phases [x] after work completes) - `implementation-summary.md` (NEW \u2014 canonical L1 template + \"Files Changed\" + \"Commit Handoff\" sections) - `description.json` + `graph-metadata.json` (NEW \u2014 generate via spec-kit scripts if available, else minimal hand-authored stubs) Modified files (with line-precise edits): - `.opencode/specs/.../011-rerank-model-fit-investigation/research/phase2-bench/run-phase2-smoke.sh` (path-extraction hardening in Python heredoc) - `.opencode/specs/.../004-extended-bake-off/evidence/run-extended-bake-off-with-hybrid-rerank.sh` (same hardening applied) - `.opencode/specs/.../011-rerank-model-fit-investigation/research/phase2-bench/README.md` (corrected fixture as canonical reference) - `.opencode/specs/.../002-spec-memory-stack/004-spec-memory-embedder-bake-off/decision-record.md` (append ADR-016) New files: - `phase2-bench/code-retrieval-fixture-audited.json` (annotated 18-probe fixture) - `phase2-bench/code-retrieval-fixture-corrected.json` (corrected variant) - `phase2-bench/phase2-comparison-corrected.md` (new bench result) - `phase2-bench/phase2-comparison-baseline-vs-corrected-delta.md` (delta analysis) - `013-bench-harness-and-fixture-audit/scratch/test_path_extraction.py` (pytest module) - `013-bench-harness-and-fixture-audit/evidence/` (any supporting artifacts you generate) ## Constraints - **Production-quality bar** \u2014 operator stated \"future-proof, hardened, strong, effective\". No shortcuts. Comprehensive test coverage. Defensive coding. Documentation rigor. - **Wide embedder support principle** \u2014 any changes you make must be embedder-agnostic. The hardened path-extraction must work with output from BGE/jina-v3/mxbai/any future reranker. - **Backward compatibility** \u2014 existing CSV/JSONL output schemas unchanged. Existing harness callers should continue to work with no changes (except seeing the new path-extraction behavior, which fixes their results). - **DO NOT use SpawnAgent.** Do all work yourself. - **DO NOT git commit. DO NOT run `ccc reset` / `ccc index`** \u2014 the DB stays as-is. - **DO NOT delete the original fixture or original phase2-comparison.md** \u2014 preserve the historical artifacts; add new ones with `-corrected` / `-audited` suffixes. - Use `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/.venv/bin/python` for any Python invocations (tests, sqlite queries). - Print `SPAWN_AGENT_USED=no` at end of run.", "candidates": [{"file_path": ".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/embedder-pluggability.md", "pre_score": 0.16076923076923078, "rerank_score": 0.10979070514440536}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/benchmark/source_template.md", "pre_score": 0.16, "rerank_score": 0.045317985117435455}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/benchmark_creation.md", "pre_score": 0.15985915492957747, "rerank_score": 0.0493558831512928}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/sk-code