.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/logs/synth.out:50353:-.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/003-memory-and-causal-runtime/003-embedder-testing-and-architecture/004-code-index-stack/011-rerank-model-fit-investigation/research/phase2-bench/jina-v3.rerank-scores.jsonl:64:{"query": "Framework: RCAF # 016/004/014 \u2014 Mirror Dedup with Canonical Preference (production-quality, future-proof) Apply sequential_thinking with >= 5 thoughts BEFORE making any edit. ## Pre-planning **Sequential_thinking mandatory**: call mcp__sequential_thinking__sequentialthinking with >= 5 thoughts covering: (1) read spec.md fully + `query.py:_dedup_and_rank_hybrid_rows()` (lines 481-515) + the existing `path_class` helpers in `indexer.py:55-93`, (2) plan the path_utils.py helper module + extract_path_stem signature, (3) plan the two-pass dedup integration in query.py without breaking the existing content_hash+line dedup, (4) plan \u22655 unit tests for both helpers and the integration, (5) plan bench gate invocation + ADR-017 + validate sequence. **Role**: You are the implementation owner for packet 016/004/014 in a 6-packet future-proofing arc on the CocoIndex retrieval pipeline. Operator principles: (a) fix code, don't bandaid with model swaps, (b) wide embedder support, best perf in all situations, (c) future-proof + hardened + strong + effective over speed. This packet is architectural cleanup \u2014 eliminates 4-mirror redundancy in the rerank candidate set so downstream packets 015 (tree-sitter chunking) and 016 (query expansion) get cleaner signal. Gate 3 PRE-ANSWERED: spec folder = `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/013-embedder-testing-and-architecture/004-code-index-stack/014-mirror-dedup-canonical-preference/`. All writes confined to that folder, the cocoindex_code source modules listed below, the bake-off decision record (ADR-017), and bench artifacts under the 014 evidence/ subdir. **Context** (read FIRST): - Spec contract: `.opencode/specs/.../014-mirror-dedup-canonical-preference/spec.md` (read fully \u2014 \u00a73 SCOPE + \u00a74 REQUIREMENTS bind the work) - Existing dedup function: `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/cocoindex_code/query.py:481-515` (`_dedup_and_rank_hybrid_rows`) - Existing path_class helper: `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/cocoindex_code/indexer.py:55-93` (`classify_path`) - Config module: `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/cocoindex_code/config.py` (env var pattern, _parse_json_string_list_env helper at lines 90-112) - Trigger evidence: `.opencode/specs/.../011-rerank-model-fit-investigation/research/cocoindex-internals-deep-dive/iterations/iteration-002.md` (4-mirror confirmation) + `iteration-005.md` (rerank-window mirror pollution) - Corrected baseline: `.opencode/specs/.../phase2-bench/phase2-comparison-corrected.md` (14/18 across all 3 lanes \u2014 the new baseline 014 must not regress) - Bench harness: `.opencode/specs/.../phase2-bench/run-phase2-smoke.sh` (supports `FIXTURE_OVERRIDE` and `OUTPUT_TAG` env vars per 013 hardening) - Existing tests to NOT regress: `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/tests/test_reranker.py`, `test_rerankers_jina_v3.py`, any other `tests/*.py` - Recently SHIPPED packet (read its impl-summary for pattern): `.opencode/specs/.../013-bench-harness-and-fixture-audit/implementation-summary.md` **Goal**: Implement R1-R10 from spec.md \u00a74. Mirror-aware two-pass dedup, canonical-mirror env config, path-stem helper, \u22655 unit tests, bench gate (re-run corrected bench \u2192 save under `evidence/phase2-comparison-014-dedup.md`), ADR-017, strict-validate PASSED. ## Steps (medium-density pre-planning, 4 ordered) 1. **Phase 1 \u2014 config + helpers (~30 min).** - Add `COCOINDEX_CANONICAL_MIRROR` (string, default `'.opencode'`) and `COCOINDEX_MIRROR_PREFIXES` (JSON list, default `[\".opencode/\", \".codex/\", \".gemini/\", \".claude/\"]`) to `config.py`. Reuse existing `_parse_json_string_list_env` for the list. Normalize trailing slash on values. Add corresponding dataclass fields + `from_env()` parsing. Empty `COCOINDEX_MIRROR_PREFIXES='[]'` is a valid value (disables mirror collapse \u2014 operator opt-out). - Create `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/cocoindex_code/path_utils.py` with three pure functions: - `extract_path_stem(file_path: str, mirror_prefixes: Iterable[str]) -> str`: strips first matching mirror prefix, returns the suffix; returns original path if no match. - `is_mirror_path(file_path: str, mirror_prefixes: Iterable[str]) -> bool`: True iff file_path starts with any prefix in the iterable. - `select_canonical_mirror_copy(candidates: Iterable, canonical_mirror: str, mirror_prefixes: Iterable[str], path_attr: str = 'file_path') -> Tuple[Optional[Any], List[Any]]`: from a list of candidates that share the same path-stem, returns (winner, losers). Winner is the canonical-mirror copy if present, else the first encountered. Stable tie-break by chunk_id or list position. - Unit tests in `mcp_server/tests/test_path_utils.py`: \u22656 tests covering stem extraction (with/without mirror match), is_mirror_path booleans, select_canonical with canonical present / canonical absent / single candidate / empty input. - Acceptance: pytest green; all helpers pure (no I/O, no logging). 2. **Phase 2 \u2014 query.py integration (~30 min).** - Modify `_dedup_and_rank_hybrid_rows()` in `query.py:481-515`. Two-pass: - **Pass A (mirror-collapse)**: group candidates by `extract_path_stem(c.file_path, mirror_prefixes)`. For each group with \u22652 entries: - If \u22652 entries are mirror paths (per `is_mirror_path`), collapse via `select_canonical_mirror_copy()`. Drop losers from the working set. - If only 1 mirror entry exists in a group, no collapse needed for that group. - Non-mirror entries pass through untouched (Pass B handles non-mirror dedup). - **Pass B (existing content_hash+line dedup)**: unchanged. - Inject config singletons (`canonical_mirror`, `mirror_prefixes`) from `config` module. Optional argument to `_dedup_and_rank_hybrid_rows()` for testability \u2014 defaulting to the config values. - If `mirror_prefixes` is empty list, Pass A is skipped entirely (operator opt-out). - Unit tests: extend `mcp_server/tests/test_query.py` OR create `test_dedup_mirrors.py` with \u22655 tests per spec \u00a73 SCOPE bullet list (4-mirror collapse \u2192 1 canonical kept; canonical absent \u2192 first encountered kept; mixed mirror + non-mirror same-stem \u2192 only mirror copies collapse; empty candidate set; single candidate). Use fake `QueryResult` instances mimicking the existing `_candidate()` test helper pattern in `test_reranker.py`. - Run full existing test suite to confirm zero regression: `cd .opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server && .venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/ -v`. - Acceptance: all tests pass, including pre-existing ones. 3. **Phase 3 \u2014 bench gate (~30 min).** - Kill any in-flight ccc daemon. Restart so the config singletons re-read env (mirror-prefix defaults apply on first daemon process). - Run `bash <repo>/.opencode/specs/.../phase2-bench/run-phase2-smoke.sh` with: - `FIXTURE_OVERRIDE=.opencode/specs/.../phase2-bench/code-retrieval-fixture-corrected.json` - `OUTPUT_TAG=-014-dedup` - `COMPARISON_OUTPUT=.opencode/specs/.../014-mirror-dedup-canonical-preference/evidence/phase2-comparison-014-dedup.md` - Diff result against `phase2-comparison-corrected.md`. Annotate ANY probe outcome differences in a sibling delta doc `evidence/phase2-comparison-013-vs-014-delta.md`. - Expectation: hit rate STAYS AT 14/18 (architectural win, not necessarily a hit-rate win). If hit rate drops, that's a regression \u2014 investigate before commit. - Acceptance: 14/18 hits or higher across all 3 lanes; p95 latency within 10% of corrected baseline; no probe regresses from hit\u2192miss. 4. **Phase 4 \u2014 ADR + docs + validate + commit handoff (~15 min).** - Append ADR-017 to `.opencode/specs/.../002-spec-memory-stack/004-spec-memory-embedder-bake-off/decision-record.md`. Cover: defect (4-mirror rerank-window pollution), fix (two-pass dedup + canonical-mirror env), env-var contract, rollback path (`COCOINDEX_MIRROR_PREFIXES='[]'`). - Update `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/cocoindex_code/README.md` (if present) with the dedup behavior section. Skip if no README exists. - Write canonical L2 `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `description.json`, `graph-metadata.json` for the 014 packet. Fill `implementation-summary.md` \u00a7\"Files Changed\" + \u00a7\"Commit Handoff\" with explicit path list. Mirror the 013 packet's doc shape. - Run `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <014-packet> --strict`. Iterate until PASSED. ## Research Question (scoped) How do we collapse 4 runtime mirror copies (`.opencode/.codex/.gemini/.claude`) of every project file into ONE canonical representative in the rerank candidate set, so downstream packets (015 chunking, 016 query expansion, 017 hybrid recalib, 018 rerank matrix re-bench) see clean signal without redundant rank slots? ## Output contract Primary deliverables in the packet folder: - `spec.md` (already exists \u2014 do NOT rewrite; patch frontmatter continuity if needed) - `plan.md` (NEW \u2014 canonical L2) - `tasks.md` (NEW \u2014 canonical L2, mark phases [x] after work completes) - `checklist.md` (NEW \u2014 L2 \u2265 requires checklist) - `implementation-summary.md` (NEW \u2014 canonical L2 + \"Files Changed\" + \"Commit Handoff\" sections) - `description.json` + `graph-metadata.json` (NEW \u2014 mirror the 013 packet's shape) - `evidence/phase2-comparison-014-dedup.md` (NEW \u2014 bench output) - `evidence/phase2-comparison-013-vs-014-delta.md` (NEW \u2014 delta analysis) Modified files (line-precise): - `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/cocoindex_code/config.py` (env vars + dataclass fields) - `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/cocoindex_code/path_utils.py` (NEW \u2014 helper module) - `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/cocoindex_code/query.py` (`_dedup_and_rank_hybrid_rows` two-pass) - `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/tests/test_path_utils.py` (NEW) - `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/tests/test_dedup_mirrors.py` (NEW \u2014 or extend test_query.py if it exists) - `.opencode/specs/.../002-spec-memory-stack/004-spec-memory-embedder-bake-off/decision-record.md` (append ADR-017) - `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/cocoindex_code/README.md` (only if exists) ## Constraints - **Production-quality bar** \u2014 operator stated \"future-proof, hardened, strong, effective\". Comprehensive test coverage. Defensive coding. Documentation rigor. - **Backward compatibility** \u2014 `COCOINDEX_MIRROR_PREFIXES='[]'` must disable mirror collapse cleanly. Pre-existing test suite must keep passing. - **Wide embedder support principle** \u2014 the dedup logic must be embedder-agnostic and reranker-agnostic. It operates on candidates' file_path strings, not on embedding vectors. - **DO NOT use SpawnAgent.** Do all work yourself. - **DO NOT git commit. DO NOT run `ccc reset` / `ccc index`** (the bge-code-v1 DB is built and reusable). - **DO NOT delete or break the 013 corrected baseline artifacts** \u2014 the 014 bench comparison reads them. - Use `.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/mcp_server/.venv/bin/python` for any Python invocations. - Print `SPAWN_AGENT_USED=no` at end of run.", "candidates": [{"file_path": ".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/embedder-pluggability.md", "pre_score": 0.16805555555555557, "rerank_score": 0.02247980423271656}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/mirror_drift_policy.md", "pre_score": 0.16129032258064518, "rerank_score": -0.05747005343437195}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/intake-contract.md", "pre_score": 0.16111111111111112, "rerank_score": 0.02413852885365486}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/sk-code/assets/opencode/checklists/spec_folder_authoring.md", "pre_score": 0.1609375, "rerank_score": -0.02402603253722191}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/references/ccc-bridge-integration.md", "pre_score": 0.1606060606060606, "rerank_score": -0.054948195815086365}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/references/tool_reference.md", "pre_score": 0.16044776119402987, "rerank_score": 0.26006460189819336}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/references/cross_cli_playbook.md", "pre_score": 0.16, "rerank_score": -0.10207881778478622}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/embedder-pluggability.md", "pre_score": 0.15958904109589042, "rerank_score": -0.023418059572577477}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/references/tool_reference.md", "pre_score": 0.15921052631578947, "rerank_score": -0.000947100343182683}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/references/downstream_adoption_checklist.md", "pre_score": 0.15909090909090912, "rerank_score": -0.11321122199296951}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/references/downstream_adoption_checklist.md", "pre_score": 0.15897435897435896, "rerank_score": -0.1079854741692543}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/benchmark_creation.md", "pre_score": 0.158641975308642, "rerank_score": -0.05781266465783119}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/benchmark/source_template.md", "pre_score": 0.15823529411764706, "rerank_score": -0.021790605038404465}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/references/tool_reference.md", "pre_score": 0.15813953488372096, "rerank_score": 0.10269114375114441}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/benchmark_creation.md", "pre_score": 0.15804597701149425, "rerank_score": -0.05190514400601387}, {"file_path": ".opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/references/tool_reference.md",