.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/deepseek/logs/iter-003.out:18:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780129091935,"sessionID":"ses_1880a546fffegerjZR6oUL4Sqp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_TA2F3CzftC4tOMhqWlQV3950","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-001.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-001.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Iteration 001 — Lane C \"skill-benchmark\": scoring dimensions for real-world utilization (RQ1) + external prior art (RQ7)\n2: \n3: > Model: opus · Iteration 1 of 5 · LEAF (no sub-dispatch) · Read-only research\n4: > Web note: `WebSearch`/`WebFetch` were permission-gated in this background context (denied, not retried). External prior-art citations below are drawn from established knowledge and given as canonical URLs **flagged `[web-unverified]`**; a later iteration with web access should confirm exact metric names/numbers. All repo citations are first-hand from files read this iteration.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## Focus\n9: \n10: RQ1 — define the scoring dimensions for benchmarking a SKILL's **real-world utilization** (how AIs actually discover and use it at the right moments), distinct from (a) Lane A's agent-file 5-dim scoring, (b) sk-doc doc-shape/DQI validation, and (c) manual testing playbooks. Five candidate dimensions: routing/activation accuracy, unprompted reference/asset discovery, efficiency/bottlenecks, usefulness via skill-on/off ablation, structural connectivity.\n11: \n12: RQ7 — map how tool/skill discoverability and routing are evaluated externally (retrieval precision/recall, tool-selection accuracy, ablation, LLM-as-judge, agent-eval harnesses) so Lane C reuses proven metrics rather than inventing them.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Actions Taken\n17: \n18: 1. Read the target skill `deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md` (full) — captured the two co-equal lanes, the three pluggable seams, the smart-router (`INTENT_SIGNALS`/`RESOURCE_MAP`/`load_if_available`), the Lane A 5-dimension framework, and Lane B's pluggable scorer/grader.\n19: 2. Read `system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md` (full) — captured how skills are routed *today* (`advisor_recommend` confidence scoring, lane weights, `advisor_validate` baselines, the `manual_testing_playbook/`), and the same smart-router orphan/dead-key surface.\n20: 3. Grepped `sk-doc/SKILL.md` — confirmed sk-doc owns **document quality (DQI)** and structural/template enforcement (`extract_structure.py`, `validate_document.py`), i.e. static doc shape, not runtime behavior.\n21: 4. Globbed the 121 sibling packet (`121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode`) — confirmed the build template: `001-mode-selector-design` (decision-record) → `002-implementation-deep-research` → `003-build-benchmark-mode` → hardening review. Lane C should follow the same packet arc.\n22: 5. Synthesized RQ1 dimensions against RQ7 external metric families.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Findings (each cited)\n27: \n28: ### F1 — The Lane C gap is real: no existing surface measures runtime utilization\n29: \n30: Three existing surfaces all measure **static artifact shape**, never **behavioral use**:\n31: \n32: - **Lane A 5-dim** scores the agent *file*: Structural Integrity (0.20), Rule Coherence (0.25), Integration Consistency (0.25), Output Quality (0.15), System Fitness (0.15) — \"template compliance,\" \"ALWAYS/NEVER rules align,\" \"mirrors in sync,\" \"frontmatter complete.\" All are read-the-file checks. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:252-262]\n33: - **sk-doc** owns DQI + structure/template enforcement via `extract_structure.py`/`validate_document.py` — \"structure, metrics, DQI, and checklist data.\" Static. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:216,355,424]\n34: - **manual_testing_playbook** is \"deterministic operator scenarios\" — human-run, not an automated measure of in-the-wild AI behavior. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:84]\n35: \n36: None answers Lane C's question: *when an AI faces a real task, does it activate this skill at the right moment, open the right reference without being told the path, do so efficiently, and is it measurably better off for having the skill?* That is a behavioral/causal question requiring run-time fixtures + ablation, not parsing. This is the defensible distinct charter for Lane C.\n37: \n38: ### F2 — Dimension 1: Routing / Activation Accuracy (does it fire when it should, stay silent when it shouldn't)\n39: \n40: Sub-metrics:\n41: - **Activation recall** — of N prompts that *should* route here, fraction the advisor/hook surfaces above the 0.8 confidence threshold. (The advisor already emits a confidence score per skill; reuse it.) [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:70-72]\n42: - **Activation precision / false-activation rate** — of prompts that should *not* route here, how often it incorrectly fires (over-triggering pollutes context).\n43: - **Abstention / boundary correctness** — on out-of-scope prompts, does it correctly NOT activate? The skill literally ships a \"When NOT to Use\" list and a \"do not use as a replacement for the target skill\" rule — those become negative fixtures. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:66-72; .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:51]\n44: - **Near-neighbor confusion** — distinguishing the skill from siblings. Live evidence this is a real failure mode: this very session's advisor brief reported `ambiguous: sk-code 0.93/0.16 vs deep-research 0.93/0.16` — a tie collision between two skills. [SOURCE: UserPromptSubmit hook context, this session]\n45: \n46: RQ7 prior art:\n47: - **MetaTool** frames exactly this as *tool-usage awareness* (should any tool be used) + *tool selection* (which one), including \"selection with similar tools,\" \"scenario-based selection,\" and \"reliability\" (abstain when no suitable tool). [SOURCE: https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.03128 `[web-unverified]`]\n48: - **Berkeley Function Calling Leaderboard (BFCL)** makes *relevance/irrelevance detection* — correctly abstaining when no function applies — a first-class scored category. Maps directly to activation precision/abstention. [SOURCE: https://gorilla.cs.berkeley.edu/blogs/8_berkeley_function_calling_leaderboard.html `[web-unverified]`]\n49: - Standard classification framing: precision / recall / F1 + a skill-vs-skill confusion matrix.\n50: \n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 170. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Iteration 001 — Lane C \"skill-benchmark\": scoring dimensions for real-world utilization (RQ1) + external prior art (RQ7)\n\n> Model: opus · Iteration 1 of 5 · LEAF (no sub-dispatch) · Read-only research\n> Web note: `WebSearch`/`WebFetch` were permission-gated in this background context (denied, not retried). External prior-art citations below are drawn from established knowledge and given as canonical URLs **flagged `[web-unverified]`**; a later iteration with web access should confirm exact metric names/numbers. All repo citations are first-hand from files read this iteration.\n\n---\n\n## Focus\n\nRQ1 — define the scoring dimensions for benchmarking a SKILL's **real-world utilization** (how AIs actually discover and use it at the right moments), distinct from (a) Lane A's agent-file 5-dim scoring, (b) sk-doc doc-shape/DQI validation, and (c) manual testing playbooks. Five candidate dimensions: routing/activation accuracy, unprompted reference/asset discovery, efficiency/bottlenecks, usefulness via skill-on/off ablation, structural connectivity.\n\nRQ7 — map how tool/skill discoverability and routing are evaluated externally (retrieval precision/recall, tool-selection accuracy, ablation, LLM-as-judge, agent-eval harnesses) so Lane C reuses proven metrics rather than inventing them.\n\n---\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n1. Read the target skill `deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md` (full) — captured the two co-equal lanes, the three pluggable seams, the smart-router (`INTENT_SIGNALS`/`RESOURCE_MAP`/`load_if_available`), the Lane A 5-dimension framework, and Lane B's pluggable scorer/grader.\n2. Read `system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md` (full) — captured how skills are routed *today* (`advisor_recommend` confidence scoring, lane weights, `advisor_validate` baselines, the `manual_testing_playbook/`), and the same smart-router orphan/dead-key surface.\n3. Grepped `sk-doc/SKILL.md` — confirmed sk-doc owns **document quality (DQI)** and structural/template enforcement (`extract_structure.py`, `validate_document.py`), i.e. static doc shape, not runtime behavior.","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-001.md","time":{"start":1780129091928,"end":1780129091934}},"id":"prt_e77f64ce5001UDWZD7yAruVJli","sessionID":"ses_1880a546fffegerjZR6oUL4Sqp","messageID":"msg_e77f63471001EbFDwhh05WXeoe"}}
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/iterations/iteration-001.md:10:1. **Read deep-agent-improvement SKILL.md** — mapped the skill's two co-equal lanes (Agent-Improvement / Model-Benchmark), three pluggable seams (candidate-source, dispatcher, scorer), smart router (INTENT_SIGNALS, RESOURCE_MAP, RUNTIME_ASSETS), lane-aware references/assets organization, loop-host.cjs entry point with `--mode` flag, and the 5-dimension scoring rubric.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/logs/iter-001.out:20:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780128182321,"sessionID":"ses_18818249cffeInllmWUcVkPFl1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_function_d9o8ac6jmgq3_2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research","pattern":"skill.*benchmark|router.*test|routing.*accuracy|unprompted.*discovery|tool.*selection"},"output":"Found 80 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/logs/iter-001.out:\n  Line 4: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128158678,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18818249cffeInllmWUcVkPFl1\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_r6hfuyah5s92_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: deep-agent-improvement\\n3: description: \\\"Evaluator-first bounded agent improvement: 5-dim scoring, dynamic profiling, packet-local candidates, guarded promotion.\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep]\\n5: version: 1.9.0.0\\n6: triggers:\\n7:   - deep-agent-improvement\\n8:   - agent improvement loop\\n9:   - bounded agent improvement\\n10:   - 5-dimension scoring\\n11:   - integration scanner\\n12:   - dynamic profiling\\n13:   - model-benchmark mode\\n14:   - benchmark a model or prompt framework\\n15: ---\\n16: \\n17: <!-- Keywords: deep-agent-improvement, deep-agent-improvement, agent-improvement, benchmark-harness, score-candidate, promote-candidate, rollback-candidate -->\\n18: \\n19: # Recursive Agent: Evaluator-First Improvement Orchestrator\\n20: \\n21: Evaluator-first workflow for testing whether a bounded agent surface can be improved without immediately mutating the source of truth. It combines packet-local candidates, deterministic scoring, repeatable benchmarks, and explicit promotion or rollback gates.\\n22: \\n23: ---\\n24: \\n25: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n26: \\n27: ### Two Co-Equal Lanes\\n28: \\n29: This skill supports two co-equal use-case lanes that share the same candidate, dispatcher, and scorer seams:\\n30: \\n31: | Lane | Pick when | Command |\\n32: | --- | --- | --- |\\n33: | **Lane A: Agent-Improvement** | You want to improve a bounded agent `.md` file | `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` |\\n34: | **Lane B: Model-Benchmark** | You want to be...\n  Line 5: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128158681,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18818249cffeInllmWUcVkPFl1\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_r6hfuyah5s92_2\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: sk-doc\\n3: description: \\\"Markdown and OpenCode component specialist: doc quality, content optimization, component scaffolds, install guides, playbooks.\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: [Bash, Edit, Glob, Grep, Read, Task, Write]\\n5: version: 1.5.0.0\\n6: ---\\n7: \\n8: <!-- Keywords: sk-doc, markdown-quality, skill-creation, document-validation, ascii-flowchart, llms-txt, content-optimization, extract-structure -->\\n9: \\n10: # Documentation Creation Specialist - Unified Markdown & Component Management\\n11: \\n12: Unified specialist providing: (1) Document quality pipeline with structure enforcement and content optimization, (2) OpenCode component creation (skills, agents, commands) with scaffolding, validation and packaging, (3) ASCII flowchart creation for visualizing workflows, (4) Install guide creation for setup documentation and (5) Feature catalog and manual testing playbook creation for inventory and validation packages.\\n13: \\n14: **Core Principle**: Structure first, then content, then quality.\\n15: \\n16: **Architecture**: Scripts handle deterministic parsing/metrics. AI handles quality judgment and recommendations.\\n17: \\n18: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n19: \\n20: ### Use Case: Document Quality Management\\n21: \\n22: Enforce markdown structure, optimize content for AI assistants, validate quality through script-assisted AI analysis.\\n23: \\n24: **README Creation** - Use `readme_template.md` + `readme_creation.md` when:\\n25: - Creating new README for any folder or project\\n26: - User requests \\\"create a RE...\n  Line 6: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128158895,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18818249cffeInllmWUcVkPFl1\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_r6hfuyah5s92_3\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: system-skill-advisor\\n3: description: Routes non-trivial requests to matching skills through standalone MCP metadata and stable advisor tool ids.\\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep]\\n5: version: 0.1.0\\n6: trigger_phrases:\\n7:   - \\\"skill advisor\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"gate 2 routing\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"advisor_recommend\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"advisor_status\\\"\\n11:   - \\\"which skill should handle this\\\"\\n12:   - \\\"route this request to a skill\\\"\\n13:   - \\\"system skill advisor\\\"\\n14: keywords:\\n15:   - skill-routing\\n16:   - gate-2\\n17:   - advisor-mcp\\n18:   - legacy-tool-bridge\\n19:   - skill-graph\\n20:   - semantic-lane\\n21: intent_signals:\\n22:   - \\\"Gate 2 skill routing\\\"\\n23:   - \\\"advisor_recommend native MCP routing\\\"\\n24:   - \\\"advisor_status freshness check\\\"\\n25:   - \\\"which skill should handle this request\\\"\\n26:   - \\\"run the skill advisor hook\\\"\\n27: ---\\n28: \\n29: <!-- Keywords: system-skill-advisor, skill-advisor, advisor_recommend, advisor_status, advisor_rebuild, advisor_validate, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_query, skill_graph_status, skill_graph_validate, skill_graph_propagate_enhances, cross-skill-edges, gate-2-routing, standalone-mcp, legacy-tool-bridge, skill-graph -->\\n30: \\n31: # System Skill Advisor\\n32: \\n33: <!-- sk-doc-template: skill_md -->\\n34: \\n35: Routes non-trivial user requests to the right skill through the standalone Skill Advisor MCP package.\\n36: \\n37: ---\\n38: \\n39: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n40: \\n41: Use this skill when the work is a...\n  Line 7: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128159017,\"sessionID\":\"ses_18818249cffeInllmWUcVkPFl1\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_function_r6hfuyah5s92_4\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/**\"},\"output\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/context-index.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/timeline.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Pub