## Focus
docs-vs-code + completion claims

## Findings
P1, `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/graph-metadata.json:40`, Parent graph metadata still reports `derived.status` as `planned`, while the parent spec and child graph metadata mark the packet/phases complete. This can mislead resume/search/status consumers even though the implementation docs are closed. Fix: regenerate or patch parent `graph-metadata.json` so `derived.status` is `complete`.

P2, `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:3`, The parent spec frontmatter still maps rename/build/docs to phases `002/003/004`, but the current phase table uses `003/004/005`. Fix: update the description to match the current phase numbering.

P2, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md:403`, The catalog says Lane C weights live in `default_profile.json`, but the scorer hardcodes `WEIGHTS` and `default_profile.json` explicitly says it is not yet consumed. Fix: state that weights are hardcoded today and the profile is forward-looking.

P2, `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:16`, The header comment still lists D1-inter advisor scoring as follow-on, while the implementation supports opt-in `--advisor-mode=python`. Fix: remove D1-inter from the follow-on list and leave only live dispatch/trace plus D4 ablation.

P2, `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/006-deep-review/review/review-report.md:6`, The severity summary says `0 P0 / 4 P1 / 6 P2`, but the same report says all 11 findings were applied and lists F-01 through F-11. Fix: reconcile the count, either by updating the summary or merging/removing the extra registry item.

## Verdict
Remediation mostly held, but one completion-metadata contradiction and four documentation/count drifts remain.
Review verdict: CONDITIONAL

